title: carrot and celery casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs, drain and stir in butter or margarine.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, cut round steak lengthwise in half, then slice in 1/8 inch slices.
In small bowl, stir flour, dry mustard, pepper and mushrooms with their liquid; stir until well blended.
In large skillet, over medium high heat, cook steak in broth about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir in mushroom mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through but do not boil. To serve, arrange meat mixture and noodles on warm platter; sprinkle parsley over meat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Put ingredients into a saucepan and heat to the simmering point, stirring regularly to keep from burning.
Be sure cheese is all stirred in.
Serve warm-to-hot with tortilla chips, etc.

title: tomato basil linguine
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients. Let stand at room
temperature 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cook linguine according to package directions; drain. Toss linguine with cheese mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: creamy pineapple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients.
Add to cabbage mixture, tossing gently. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese on top.

title: noodles and rice
directions: Simmer rice and noodles in butter until brown.
Put in baking dish and add all of the soups and mushrooms.
Mix and cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Stir refried beans until smooth.
Spread beans on large platter.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning.
Spread sour cream mixture on beans.
Layer with guacamole dip.
Mix together tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Spread over guacamole dip. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: maryland black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts to sugar-egg mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Then add oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: el dorado dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice, Worcestershire and steak sauces, pepper, celery salt and hot pepper sauce in bowl; mix well.
Serve dip with a tray of carrot and celery sticks, fingers or sliced cucumbers, cauliflower buds.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix the 2 cans of soup and chicken together.
Add the milk. Stir until mixed well.
Pour mixture in a square Pyrex dish.
Top with the chow mein noodles.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a mixing bowl; add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir into egg mixture.
Batter will be stiff.
Add chopped nuts and apples.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into a greased casserole dish set into a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Cover with the reserved cup of cracker crumbs and put back into oven until golden brown.

title: mrs. clark caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, Karo syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn.
Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Make a sauce of egg, slightly beaten, and sugar.
Mix.
Add oleo and flour.
Beat until smooth and add juice drained from can of pineapple.
Cook over medium heat until thick and smooth.
Cool while you cut up the marshmallows.
Mix with the pineapple.
Pour sauce over and mix all together.
Chill until serving time.

title: spicy lasagna roll-ups
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add onion, basil, bay leaf, 1/2 of garlic and pepper. Cook uncovered until onion is soft, about 5 minutes. Remove 2 tablespoons of mixture and set aside. Add chopped chicken. Stir for 3 minutes. Reduce heat. Add tomatoes and tomato paste. Cook uncovered 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Set aside.

title: oven-fried fish(300 calories)
directions: Combine margarine, lemon juice and spices.
Dredge fish in margarine mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Spread oil or spray Pam in a 9 x 13-inch dish for baking.
(I line pan with foil for easy clean up.)
Put fish in pan.
Spoon remaining margarine mixture over fish.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes at 475° or until done. Don't overcook fish.

title: garlic baked beans
directions: Place beans in a bowl and cover completely with water.
Soak 12 hours.
Drain beans and transfer to ovenproof casserole.
Cover completely with fresh water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add bouquet garni and cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet on medium-high.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic 3 minutes.
Add remaining Scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucini; toss and heat through.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook, cool, and chop chicken into small pieces.
Cook and drain egg noodles.
Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients well.
Add shrimp; cut in small pieces.
Fresh shrimp is much better.
Mix lightly and chill.
You may add a second package of Italian salad dressing mix for a zippier dip.

title: st. agnes hospital baked chicken reubenoff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix baking mix, milk, oil, 1 tablespoon dressing and eggs.
Spread in dish. Layer remaining ingredients, except onions, on egg mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Top with onions and bake 3 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and vinegar in saucepan and heat until vinegar sauce starts to thicken.
Add beet juice gradually and cook until thick.
Heat beets in top of double boiler.
Drain liquid from hot beets and add vinegar sauce and keep hot over hot water for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in greased dish.
Mix chicken, curry powder and soup.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese, then sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and follow recipe on box; let cool.
Make pudding per directions on box.

title: turkey picatta
directions: Sprinkle fresh turkey with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown the turkey lightly in the butter and olive oil.
Remove the turkey to a platter and keep warm.

title: autumn delight
directions: Generously grease 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Slightly fry bacon; drain and discard fat.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions.

Place in alternate layers in casserole the onions, potatoes and bacon. Mix soup, tomato paste and seasonings and pour over casserole. Cover casserole and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender and slightly brown.
Serves 6 (depending on appetites!).

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save 1 1/2 c. juice. Mix with Tang and vanilla pudding. Drain Mandarin oranges and stir in fruit, gently. Let set overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: In bowl, mix granulated sugar and 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Quarter each biscuit and drop into bowl to coat thoroughly (do a few at a time).
Toss coated pieces into a greased Bundt pan.
Any remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture can be sprinkled over pieces.

title: coconut pie #3
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mix milk, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix all dry ingredients with milk, eggs and vanilla.
Put oleo in and cook over low heat until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add a pinch of salt and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread on top of pie.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake until brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
When warm, peel and cut in half, putting yolks in bowl. Set aside egg whites (halves).
In a bowl, mix yolks and the mayonnaise, mustard, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and onions until smooth.
Now place about 1 teaspoon of the mixture into each egg half.
When finished, sprinkle paprika on top of eggs lightly.

title: swedish almond rusks(biscuitini - cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, beat shortening until creamy. Add sugar, about 1/3 at a time, beating well after each addition.
When well blended, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in almond extract.
Mix in dry ingredients, about 1/3 at a time, alternating with sour cream (mixture will be very stiff).
Mix in almonds.

title: baked zucchini sticks
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise in quarters, then in half crosswise. Dip into beaten egg, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Coat the quarters with a mixture of Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted butter over all. Bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown, in a 400° oven.
Can be served as finger food or vegetable with a meal.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Use amount right for you.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
Mix mayonnaise with cottage cheese and milk.
Then add pineapple and nuts.
Add the mayonnaise, cottage cheese and milk mixture along with pineapple and nuts to the jello.
Refrigerate and let congeal.

title: german chop suey
directions: Brown pork steak and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with Chinese noodles (cook until semi-soft).
Dot with butter.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk and prunes; beat until blended. Add sugar, flour, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, pecans and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco tarts
directions: Layer in casserole and bake about 15 minutes for 350°.

title: mock enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger; drain grease or boil chicken.
Take off the bone.
Mix mushroom soup with a little milk.
In a cake pan or baking dish, layer ingredients, corn tortillas, hamburger, chile, cheese and soup.
You will get two layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup mix with 4 cups hot water.
Put chicken parts on top of rice and pour soup mix over chicken and rice.
Will be quite juicy.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until chicken is done.
Serves 6.

title: mother's custard
directions: I beat the eggs (all but the 6 whites), sugar and vanilla; put in a large pan.
I sit that in my roasting pan filled with water. I stir every few minutes.
I cook it until it begins to thicken, about 2 hours or more.
Beat 6 egg whites stiff and put them in custard.
I take my hand mixer and beat the custard.
When it gets cold it is ready to drink.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook slowly for 6 minutes in saucepan (or may be cooked in microwave; stir every 2 minutes), stirring frequently.
When mixture cools slightly, add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir until gooey and form into small balls.
Put powdered sugar in sack and shake.
Or you may place powdered sugar in a medium bowl and roll.
Place in airtight container.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice, then carrots, onions and celery.
Place chicken breasts on top of vegetables.
Mix soups and water in bowl.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, plain flour, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and cook in a double boiler until mixture bubbles.
Have the eggs separated and beat the egg yolks until smooth.
Add the egg yolks to the mixture, stirring constantly while adding.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla; set aside.
When cool, pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made of egg whites and bake until meringue is brown.

title: large goofy cake
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: light macaroni ring salad
directions: Cook macaroni rings according to instructions.
Drain and cool.
Add onion, peas, diced eggs, seasonings and salad dressing mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.
May be decorated with tomato wedges or sliced hard-boiled eggs.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion until golden; add meat and seasoning.
Brown.
Add soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and seasonings.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake at 350°.
Good dish for children.

title: christmas logs
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, eggs, pecans and dates.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add vanilla, then pour over Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
When cool enough, shape into logs and roll in coconut.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Spread
half
of
mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese (Cheddar).
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Sprinkle with more cheese and bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop up
the chipped beef and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients
together
and roll into ball.	Now roll ball into beef until	it is covered.	Place in covered container or foil and place in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: cocoa nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl; beat 30 seconds on medium speed, scraping sides and bottom constantly.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook 2 minutes on High.
Stir.
Continue to cook to 300° on thermometer.
Stir occasionally at 300°.
Add 1 teaspoon soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
When cooled, break into pieces.

title: marinated tomatoes(fresh homegrown tomatoes and herbs make a delicious salad.)
directions: In a deep dish, put the tomatoes, vinegar, oil and herbs.
Let set in refrigerator (4 hours to overnight) a long time?
Turn every now and then to baste the tomatoes well.
Serve with sliced cucumbers on salad plate.
Spoon some of the oil over each. Yields 4 servings.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, cook in crock-pot all day.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as stated on box directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: golden door cheesecake
directions: With blender or food processor, puree Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, sugar, eggs or substitute, yogurt, vanilla and lemon peel until smooth and thick.
Blend in flour and cornstarch well.
Pour into an 8-inch spring-form pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake about 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill until cold; decorate with choice of fruit.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients except hens and additional melted butter.
Sprinkle cavity of each hen with salt.
Stuff rice mixture into cavities of hens.
Loosely cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue to bake for 1 hour, basting occasionally with butter.
Yields 6 servings.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Very good!

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Place all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour in pie pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Make your own crust or purchase ready made.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Layer bread and sausage in oblong casserole dish.
Pour mixture of eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt and pepper into the pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with cheese and cook at 350° until brown (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).
Serve with biscuits or rolls.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: Put meat on sticks.
In one bowl, combine salt, bread crumbs and pepper.
In another bowl, combine egg and milk.
Mix in egg and milk, then salt-bread crumbs-pepper mixture.
Brown meat slowly in shortening; put in baking pan.
Dissolve bouillon and water, then pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and cook 15 minutes.
Turn meat; cook another 15 minutes.

title: zucchini and sausage
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet. Brown sausage. Add onion, celery, pepper, garlic, oregano and pepper. Cook and stir until vegetables are almost tender. Add squash and tomatoes. Cook and stir until zucchini is just tender. Sprinkle with herb seasoning. This is great with cornbread or garlic bread.

title: good corn bread
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 450° until brown.

title: apple-cranberry-mincemeat pie
directions: Toss apple slices, 1 tablespoon flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon until apple slices are coated; set aside. Cook cranberries and 1/4 cup sugar over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, then drain. Spoon mincemeat into prepared pie crust and top with apples. Then spoon cranberries over apples and sprinkle with crumb topping. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with 1 slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with chipped beef, then arrange chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: peach tart
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 9-inch glass pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer peaches in spiral in pie plate.

title: dilled trout
directions: Clean, wash and dry fish.
Cut fish almost through lengthwise and spread open.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in frypan.
Add dill weed.
Place fish in a single layer, flesh side down, in the hot dill butter.
Fry at moderate heat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Turn.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes longer until fish flakes easily.;
Place fish on platter; keep warm.
Turn heat very low and stir in lemon juice.
Pour sauce over fish.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Combine ketchup, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Heat on low heat.
Cut hot dogs in 1-inch slices and heat slowly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Stir well.
Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: louis pappas famous greek salad
directions: Line a large platter with the outside lettuce leaves and place 3 cups of the potato salad in a mound in the center of the platter.
Cover with remaining lettuce which has been shredded. Arrange the roka or watercress on top of this.
Place the tomato wedges around the outer edges of salad with a few on the top and place the cucumber wedges in between the tomatoes, making a solid base of the salad.
Place the avocado slices around the outside. Slices of Feta cheese should be arranged on the top of the salad with the green pepper slices over all.
On the very top, place the sliced beets with a shrimp on each beet slice and an anchovy filet on the shrimp.
The olives, peppers and green onions can be arranged as desired.
The entire salad is then sprinkle with the vinegar (more may be used) and then with the blended oil. Sprinkle the oregano over all and serve at once.
Garlic toasted Greek bread is served with this salad and Louis Pappas called this a "salad for 4 persons."

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut dates and pecans.
Use an angel food cake pan.
Grease pan good and use wax paper at bottom of pan.
Decorate top with some pecans and cherries.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Place ingredients in a Ziploc bag 4 to 8 hours.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and chill 3 hours.
Pinch off into small balls and chill again until firm.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate and paraffin mixture and place on waxed paper to set.
Store in tightly closed container in refrigerator.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: Put oleo in a 9 x 15-inch pan in oven and melt.
Mix all remaining ingredients but peaches together and pour over oleo (do not stir).
Add peaches and juice on top (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except pie shell, and add to oleo-sugar mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 12 minutes at 425°.
Turn down to 350° for rest of the hour.

title: christmas punch(party punch)
directions: Mix together and chill.
Freeze some to put in punch bowl first and pour the rest over it (helps keep punch chilled). Serves 24 to 30 people.

title: aebleskiver(danish pancake balls)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk and beat until batter is smooth.
Fry in aebleskiver pan.
Heat pan over medium heat; melt one teaspoon margarine in each hole.
Fill holes completely with batter; let bake a few minutes, then turn with a fork or an ice pick.
Fry until golden brown.

title: yeast coffee cake
directions: Scald milk, then add margarine.
Set aside to cool.
With electric beater, mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk and yeast. Beat in 2 cups of flour.
Remaining flour is mixed in by hand with strong spoon.
Mix for about 3 minutes.
Let rise until double. Punch down and put in 2 (9-inch) pans (greased).
The dough will be a little sticky, so slightly grease your fingers when placing in pan.
Let rise again for about 1 hour.

title: chicken, artichoke hearts and mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and saute chicken strips and mushrooms 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika, pepper and flour over ingredients and stir well until flour is no longer visible.
Add broth and sherry, stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir in artichoke hearts; cook another minute and serve over rice or pasta.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine soup, salad dressing, curry powder, mushrooms and lemon juice in bowl.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and turkey and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Line pan with chips.
Pour in meat and onion.
Top with soup, beans, sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle a few chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and stir until boiling, then simmer, stirring often for 1 hour (will thicken as it cools).
Sprinkle more cinnamon and nutmeg on top.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pudding cups
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Divide cookie crumbs into 8 (4-inch) custard cups, approximately 1 1/2 tablespoons per cup, and gently press crumbs into bottom of each cup.
Set aside while preparing remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
vegetables until done;
drain well.
Place cooked vegetables in casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup shredded
Swiss cheese, sour cream and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in pan over
low
heat until mixture is smooth and cheese has melted. Pour mixture over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Remove from oven.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese and French fried onions.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Place cooked noodles in large casserole.
Add cream of mushroom soup, copped turkey or chicken and mushrooms.
Mix well, add salt and pepper to season.
Cover top with shredded cheese. Place in oven and heat for 1/2
hour at 350°.
If needed, you can add milk, if too dry.

title: cold chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, onion and lemon juice together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed chips and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add vinegar and egg; cook over boiling water on low heat until thick.
Pour over fruit.

title: italian beef
directions: Fry steak in a heavy skillet with lots of butter, then spread with salt and mustard.
Cook over a low heat until very tender. Place on a hot platter.
Pour a large cup of strong coffee in the frypan; let it boil up one time.
Pour it over the steak and serve quickly.
Serve with chopped, pickled walnuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
Add some salt and pepper for taste.
Combine all the ingredients.
Top with saltines and butter. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: jack daniel's chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
eggs, sugar, butter, syrup, vanilla and whiskey.
Mix well, then strain.
Sprinkle chocolate chips
over
the
bottom
of the unbaked pie crust; cover
with pecans.
Pour filling over chips and pecans.
Bake for
40 minutes
or
until knife inserted halfway between the center and the
edge comes out clean.	Set aside for at least 30 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in
a Pyrex baking dish.
Pour in the sliced peaches.
Pour milk over peaches.
Mix together: Bisquick, sugar. Pour over peaches.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until firm but tender.
Combine with all ingredients and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except tortillas).
Fill each tortilla with a tablespoon of filling.
Roll up and line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(I use microwave-safe dish with cover.) Spread remaining ingredients evenly over all tortillas.
Grate a thin layer of Cheddar cheese.
(Note: Can be refrigerated at this time until ready to use, as much as 8 hours later.)

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef over medium heat until light brown.
Stir to keep loose.
Combine all other ingredients together and mix well.
Add to beef.
Stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat until beef has absorbed liquid (about 40 minutes).
Serve with cole slaw.
If a more spicy barbecue is desired, use more paprika, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, spread rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle sugar over top and jello (dry).
Make batter of flour, salt, baking powder, sugar, oil, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spoon over rhubarb.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients. Then beat next 2 ingredients together.
Pour chocolate mixture into cream cheese mixture. Blend well.
Then stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Keep frozen.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil shrimp and peel.
Chop shrimp and shallots.
In saucepan, heat soup and 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and mix with mixer until well blended.
Stir in mayonnaise until completely blended.
Add shrimp and shallots.
Pour into Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: john a's grandmama bea's three bean salad
directions: Mix all vegetable together in a large salad bowl. Lima/Butter Beans may also be added depending on taste.
Drain before adding.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Mix together in a bowl; let stand overnight in the refrigerator covered.
Will keep for several days.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Put in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press together and up sides for crust.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle in potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour in crust. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Get some slices of bread and put butter on them.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Put the bread in the oven and bake for about 10 minutes.
Then take it out of the oven and eat it up!

title: imperial cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add vinegar, soda and flour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake about 10 minutes at 325°.

title: "lo-cal" banana split cake
directions: Layer all ingredients in order.
Chill.
Divide into 4 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix together and freeze until ready to use. Add 4 to 6 quarts of ginger ale, poured over frozen punch. Serve.

title: portuguese biscuits(hard cookie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead until dough is easy to handle.
Break off pieces of dough and make a rope about 6-inches in length and about 3/8th of an inch thick.
Form a ring bringing the ends together.
Place rings on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool and store in a tin or other container with a tight lid.
May be sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar, etc.

title: lindsey's hot dog wrap-ups
directions: Spread soft butter on each side of bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Place slice of cheese on each slice.
Put a hot dog diagonally across each slice of bread and cheese.
Put oven on 375°.
Fold the opposite corners of the bread over each hot dog. Push toothpick through the bread and hot dog.
Bake about 10 minutes until brown.

title: 24 hour tossed salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread on top.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cover with bacon bits before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cook ground chuck, onions and bell pepper in a large skillet until done.
(Until meat changes color.)
Add peas and tomatoes. Mix all together and cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
With French bread or cornbread, this is a good 1 dish meal.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute celery, carrots and diced onion in butter and enough stock so that vegetables do not stick or burn.
Add Stove Top stuffing mix.
Stir until makes crumbly mixture.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan with 1/3 of honey grahams. Whisk together pudding mix and milk. Stir until mixture thickens. Add whipped topping. Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Repeat layers of graham crackers and remaining pudding. Top with remaining graham crackers. Spread with chocolate frosting. Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Combine Milky Way bars and 1/2 cup butter in medium saucepan and melt over low heat.
While candy melts, prepare batter.
Cream 1/2 cup butter and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk, stirring until smooth. Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done when tested with wooden toothpick.
Remove from oven.
Cool a few minutes and remove from pan.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin. Mix sugar, flour, and cinnamon. Spread 1/3 sugar mixture in
bottom of pastry lined pan. Fill with apples (heap-they cook down). Top with remaining sugar mixture and dot with butter. Cover with top crust. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave pecans
directions: Put pecans into baking dish, add butter and salt.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes, stirring pecans and adding a little salt.
Do this for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and cool. Store in a sealed container.
Can be eaten now or later.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from pans to cool.
Peel off paper.
Put icing on first layer, then place on next layer.
Spread remaining icing on top and sides.

title: crispy baked fish fillets
directions: Season fish with Tony's seasoning.
Add buttermilk and toss to coat.
Roll each piece in cracker crumbs.
Spray wire rack with Pam and put on cookie sheet.
Place fillets on rack.
Dribble small amount of squeeze margarine over each piece.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden color and crisp around edges.

title: kool klay
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and water.
Stir quickly, mixing well.
When clay cools, knead it with flour until soft and pliable.
Store in airtight container.

title: pink sugar corn
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients to the soft ball stage, stirring occasionally until soft ball forms in water.
Remove from heat. Add food coloring.
Pour over 6 to 8 quarts of popped corn.
Add a little at a time until all is coated.
Continue to stir until corn separates and sugars.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix like cookie dough, rather soft.
Roll thin.
Cut and bake on greased cookie sheet in moderate oven (325° to 350°) until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up	chicken
and
layer in bottom of a large square casserole dish.
Mix
chicken
broth and cream of chicken soup together and
pour	over
chicken.	Mix
flour and pepper with milk and
melted
butter.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in oven at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.	Will be golden brown on top.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter.
Combine sugar, butter, water and syrup.
Cook over medium heat to 290° on candy thermometer.
Sprinkle half of nuts in bottom of pan.
Pour syrup over nuts.
Break up or grate chocolate over top of hot mixture and when melted, sprinkle remainder of nuts on top of chocolate.
Press in slightly.
Refrigerate until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, hot water, and syrup in a medium pot and cook to a hard boil.
Add the raw Spanish peanuts and cook until the syrup turns golden.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and baking soda.
Quickly stir together and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into edible pieces.
Store in an air-tight container.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Combine all ingredients, except butter and cereal flakes, and put in baking dish. Melt butter, and mix flakes with butter; spread on top of potato mixture. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In casserole dish, layer the ingredients as listed at least 3 times.
Sprinkle salt and pepper as desired.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
(Check at 25 minutes, then cover with foil to keep cheese from overbrowning.)
Serves 6.

title: grandma's tasty clam dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temp.
Mix all ingredients with a fork (needs elbow grease to mix well).
After thoroughly mixed, refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Tastes better if it sets over night. Take out and let stand to soften 1-1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and beat on #7 or cream setting for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes on high. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well. Add oatmeal, chips and nuts; mix well.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat over moderate heat, stirring with a spoon to break up.
Using a slotted spoon, remove meat to a bowl or plate.
Pour off all but 1 teaspoon fat from the skillet. Add onion and garlic; cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until softened.

title: lasagne pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Mix cooked turkey/beef, 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese, oregano, basil and tomato paste; spoon evenly over top.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine (save 1 tablespoon until smooth).
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each square.
Pull the corners of dough to top center of meat mixture, twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved margarine.
Dip in crushed croutons.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wild rice (veal)
directions: Brown cubed veal, onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Put into casserole and add mushroom soup, chicken-rice soup, wild rice and mushrooms.
Bake for 2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter; add cheese and blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually to butter cheese mixture.
Roll dough into long rolls 1 inch in diameter.
Refrigerate dough for several hours or overnight. Slice into 1/4-inch rounds.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased). Bake at 450° for 8 minutes or until slightly brown or not quite brown at all!

title: karo nut pie
directions: Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Fold in remaining ingredients. Put in mold or 9 X 13 pan.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Bring together to boil 2 sticks of butter, 1 cup of water and 4 tablespoons cocoa; then pour over flour and sugar mixture. Stir and add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and add nuts. Pour into a large cookie sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream flour, margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar together. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300° to 325°.
Beat eggs, lemon juice, sugar, flour and salt.
Pour over baked crust. Return to oven and bake for 25 minutes at 300° to 325°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top and cut in squares.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 3 ingredients until blended. In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center. Add buttermilk mixture, stirring until flour mixture is just moistened. Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tops are golden and muffins test done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil 4 quarts water; add noodles (salt optional) and return to a boil.
Boil uncovered 10 to 12 minutes; drain and rinse. While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef and sausage; add garlic, green pepper, onions and mushrooms.
After onion is tender, add spaghetti sauce and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Spread sauce in bottom of large ovenproof lasagna dish.
Next add noodles, meat sauce; sprinkle the 3 different cheeses on next. Continue layering in this order.
Top with lots of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Before serving, top with fresh grated parmesan cheese.
Serve with a green salad and garlic toast.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cook sugars, flour and juice until thick.
Add pineapple chunks.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with bread cubes which was coated with oleo.
Bake in 350° oven until it bubbles and bread cubes are golden brown.
This is to be served with main course.

title: strawberry parfait
directions: In bowl, stir together wafers and Fleischmann's sweet unsalted margarine; set aside.
In medium bowl, stir together sliced strawberries, yogurt and honey.
Alternately layer yogurt mixture and crumb mixture in 4 (6 ounce) parfait glasses.
Chill.
To serve, garnish with whole strawberries.

title: sugar cane fruit punch
directions: Mix ingredients well. Chill thoroughly and serve over ice. Serves 4.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Let cool. Mix all of the above ingredients together (except the tomatoes, olives and Parmesan cheese).
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Mix in cherry tomatoes, olives and cheese just before serving.

title: hawaiian tuna salad(pasta salad with a tropical twist)
directions: In medium bowl combine tuna, cooked macaroni, celery, pineapple, and grapes.
In small bowl, stir together yogurt, mayonnaise, salt, and pepper.
Gently stir yogurt mixture into tuna.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate syrup and biscuits
directions: *Or as some people call it, Chocolate Gravy...but I prefer syrup.

title: ashley's hot beef dip
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients and spread in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or celery.

title: harvest beets
directions: Let first 5 ingredients come to a boil until it thickens.
Add beets.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar with electric mixer.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt sifted together) alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Knead slightly on floured board.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter (roll very thin for crisp cookies).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° when cookies are put in oven.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir cornstarch in sugar and add to eggs and pineapple.
Place in an 8-inch casserole.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and pieces of butter.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Good side dish with ham.

title: e-z eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2 inch thick slices.
(Leave skin on.) Put olive oil in bowl and dip slices of eggplant in oil.
Be sure to cover both sides.
Press into seasoned breadcrumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place pan on middle rack in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Flip slices over and cook for another 15 minutes. Spread Italian seasoned sauce, like "Prego" on top of each slice and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and cook for 3 to 5 more minutes.
This is easy and delicious.
No fuss, little clean up.

title: golden mushroom fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, combine Bisquick mix, mushrooms, onion, pimento, salt and celery seed.
Mix together egg yolk and sour cream; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold beaten egg white into mushroom mixture.
In heavy saucepan or electric deep fat fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Transfer to rack to drain.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan and eggs.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in sauce (gravy).

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, stir 1 tablespoon mix into 1/2 cup hot water.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups tea mix.

title: self-crust egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add to well-beaten eggs.
Add milk, evaporated milk, melted butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Grease pie pan with butter.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mammy's applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop from spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: honey-coconut toast
directions: In shallow bowl, combine eggs with buttermilk, sweetener, if desired, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dip bread into egg mixture, turning on both sides.
Let stand until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Heat margarine in nonstick skillet and add bread.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over bread.
Cook, turning to brown both sides.
Transfer to nonstick baking sheet.
Spread each slice with 1/2 teaspoon honey and sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon coconut. Broil for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix together and chill until set.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Cook Duncan Hines cake mix as per directions on box.
Let cool.
When done, punch holes in top with fork and pour cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a wire whisk.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Cover with sauce and bake 350° for 1- 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook the cranberries in the water until soft.
Add sugar; cook 5 minutes more.
Pour while boiling hot over the jello.
When cool, add the remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm, then enjoy.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Prepare Jell-O pudding mix as directed on box.
Layer pudding mix, bananas and cookies.
End with bananas and cookies.
Makes a delicious dessert for diabetics!

title: easy brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl, except Reeses chips. Mix well. Spread in greased 12 X 15 pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle Reeses chips on top.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sour cream and margarine.
Beat in egg, lemon peel and juice until well combined.
Combine next 5 ingredients in separate bowl and blend into creamed mixture only until ingredients are moistened (30 to 45 seconds).
Line muffin pan with papers and spoon in batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until muffins test done with a wooden toothpick.
Let stand on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: taco surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer until creamy.
Put in large round dish or pizza pan.
(I layer mine on a pizza pan with foil.)
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped green pepper, onion, black olives, grated sharp Cheddar cheese and chopped tomatoes.

title: "melitzanes me skortho" - eggplant with garlic sauce
directions: Wash eggplants; remove stems and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt and let them stand for 30 minutes or longer.
Rinse and squeeze out the water.
Fry in oil until both sides are light brown, adding more oil if necessary.
Lay the fried pieces on absorbent paper in layers.
Slice fresh tomatoes in a pan with a little oil.
Add the crushed garlic and cook until thick.
You can use either tomato paste or tomato sauce. Put layers of eggplant and sauce in a casserole or dish. Refrigerate and serve warm or cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in ball, chopped nuts and roll top with cherries and refrigerate.

title: saffron rice
directions: Mix saffron with heated chicken broth and let sit. In heavy skillet, heat olive oil and butter on medium heat.
Add chopped onion and cook until onion is translucent (don't burn).
Add rice. Stir to coat rice with oil and butter. Add broth.
Cover pan and simmer for about 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain 1 quart dill pickles and cut in strips. Place back in jar and add all ingredients. Leave in refrigerator.
Shake often to dissolve sugar.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger well and drain.
Add onion.
Add canned spaghetti and cheese to hamburger.
Let all heat together.
Put in Pyrex dish (large one).
Place thinly sliced Velveeta cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and is slightly browned.

title: chicken filled shells
directions: Mix together the 4 ingredients. Stuff shells. Arrange in a single layer in baking dish. Stir water into soup and pour over shells. Cover with foil paper and bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Add pimentos for color.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook and skin beets.
Add sugar, salt and spices tied in bag, to vinegar and water; simmer 15 minutes.
Add beets and boil for 5 minutes.
Pack beets into jars and cover with syrup.
Seal.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until cold.
Roll in ball and press down.
Dip one side in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
When done, remove from oven and poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Then pour either caramel or pineapple topping on top of cake.
When condensed milk and topping are absorbed into holes, spread whipped topping over entire cake.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars over top of cake.
Refrigerate.
Cake may be made a day in advance.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Beat butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; fold in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on sheets.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, assemble first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Add to broccoli mixture and toss.
Serve immediately or refrigerate in airtight container.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil your chicken, celery, bell pepper, onion and broth together.
When chicken is done, add a 12 ounce package of spaghetti in broth for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 pound of Velveeta cheese to cooked spaghetti and chicken.
When cheese is melted, add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and can of Ro-Tel.
This dish can be frozen to serve at a later date.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add (melted) margarine and beaten eggs, plus vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, until firm.

title: eggless, butterless, milkless cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, water, raisins, lard, spices and salt in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes, then cool.
When cool, add baking soda dissolved in hot water.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add to liquid mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven.

title: chocolate date nut bread
directions: In small bowl, pour boiling water over dates.
Melt chocolate chips with butter.
Beat egg with milk and vanilla.
In a large bowl, combine flour, nuts, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add dates and liquid, chocolate and milk mixtures.
Mix just until blended.
Pour batter into one large or two small well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In saucepan, combine meat, tomato paste, water, taco seasoning and salsa.
Let simmer for 40 minutes.
Add cheese, stirring frequently; simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken breasts in bite-size pieces and cook until done in microwave.
Pam or grease the bottom of large casserole bowl. Place broccoli on bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle
with Parmesan cheese. Next, spread chicken over the broccoli and cheese and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.

title: slush
directions: Boil sugar in 7 cups water.
Boil 2 cups water, remove from stove and place tea bags in water for 15 minutes.
Cool ingredients and add frozen orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Mix well and freeze. Serve with sweet or sour soda.

title: garbanzo stew and dumplings
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Bring to boil using the soaking water.
Reduce heat and cook all day, until well done and liquid is of rich consistency.
Simmer the onion in margarine; sprinkle on flour and blend.
Use enough liquid from beans to make smooth.
Add to garbanzo beans and let it boil up to make a thin sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drop dumplings by tablespoons. Cover and let cook 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve immediately.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour large Bundt pan.
Cream butter with sugar on medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until well mixed.
Add cream cheese, vanilla and almond flavoring. Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each.
Beat on high speed 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon batter into Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in butter; brown hamburger and drain.
Combine hamburger, onions and cheese together.
Remove from heat.
Pour soups and enchilada sauce into medium saucepan, then bring to soft boil.
Take shells, 1 at a time, dip into sauce until soft.
Then roll meat up in shells.
When finished, pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in oven for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: enchiladas suizas
directions: Combine chicken, chiles and salsa for filling.
Mix salt with cream for sauce.
Fry each tortilla in medium-hot oil a few seconds, until it blisters and is limp.
Dip onto cream and fill with chicken mixture.
Fold and place in ungreased baking pan, flap side down.
When all tortillas are filled, pour remaining cream over them.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 12.

title: happy ham
directions: Pour beer
over ham.
Sprinkle brown sugar over ham and drizzle honey over that.
Bake 5 to 6 hours, while occasionally basting
with
sauce,
until
very	tender.
Beer takes the salty taste away and leaves a honey roasted ham.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth like shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each.
Add flour, alternating with whipping cream.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Start from cold oven; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers and dot with margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: You don't have to baste this recipe, just put in the oven.
Set the timer for 5 hours at 300°.
Place heavy foil in a large roaster; put in the shad.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add a small diced onion and place 3 strips of bacon on shad.
Wrap the foil tightly and bake.
When ready to serve, just lift the shad out of the roaster and place on serving platter.
Pull back the foil and crimp.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine ingredients, blend ice cream gently.
Stir in 2 1/2 quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar; beat in vanilla.
Add eggs, beat for 3 to 4 minutes. Combine flour, salt and soda, add to creamed mixture.
Mixture will be sticky, yet dry.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing.

title: corn casserole
directions: Spray casserole.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: taste of reality
directions: When mixing ingredients add tears of joy and tears for sorrow.
Flavor with love and kind services.
Fold in prayers, faith and enthusiasm.
Spread all into your daily life.
Blends well with human kindness.
Serve with a smile at all times, and it will satisfy the hunger of many people less fortunate than ourselves.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Brown chops on both sides. Arrange onion and potato slices around chops.
Combine orange juice, cloves, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until chops are tender.
Add apples; cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
With slotted spoon, remove meat, vegetables and apples to serving platter.
Remove and discard cloves.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Thick with cornstarch.
When ham is half baked, brush glaze on ham and return to oven and finish baking.
Always delicious.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream together cheese and butter; add remaining ingredients and mix until flour is blended.
Pinch into bits and roll into balls. Flatten each ball on greased cookie sheet using a fork and bake at 300° until light brown.
(Do not overcook!)
Yields 3 dozen.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Cream vanilla, sugar, Cool Whip and cheese together.
Spread over crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: peach pick me up
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover.
Blend until mixture is well blended.
Serve immediately in tall glasses.
This is a good pick me up for our diabetic friends.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese in small mixing bowl of electric mixer.
Set in refrigerator until almost set.
Beat with electric mixer after adding Cool Whip and nuts.
When well mixed, put into jello mold and let set.
Keep as long as you wish.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Mix well. Add flour in small amounts until well blended.
Add baking powder, salt and flavoring.
Put in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cube potatoes; cook and drain.
Add seasonings to taste, soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts, then add milk.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss in stuffing mix.
Spread half into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cabbage and onion onto stuffing.
Pour your mixture of soup, milk and mayo over cabbage.
Add cheese, then remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade chocolate sauce(for ice cream, etc.)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add salt and boiling water. Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Be very careful; it burns easily and will boil over very quickly.
Makes about 1 pint of sauce.
It will keep in the refrigerator for a long while.

title: coffee liqueur(kahlua)
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add instant coffee, vanilla and vodka.
Pour into dark bottle; cap and store in cool, dark place for 30 days.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in large 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup nuts and 1/4 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: tasty clam chowder
directions: Peel and chop potatoes and onion into pieces.
Add celery, butter, 1 cup of water and parsley.
Cook until tender; mash slightly.
Add clams and milk; heat but do not boil.
Serve with breadsticks or rolls.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil until bubbly the raisins, water and soda.
Mix together the other ingredients; combine with raisin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan. Pour melted mixture over Corn Chex.
Toss until well covered. Place 2 cups of powdered sugar in a bag along with Chex mixture and shake until well covered.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Bring tomato juice to a low boil.
Start dropping raw hamburger in; add seasonings.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix cocoa mix, coffee creamer, confectioners sugar and powdered milk.
Stir to blend.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve orange and lemon jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Refrigerate (after mixing well) until slightly thickened. Mix together (with mixer) softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and pecans.
Fold into jello mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Chill until almost firm.
Dissolve the peach jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir the peach pie filling in.
Chill until partially congealed and pour over top of other layer.

title: quick pralines
directions: In a glass bowl, combine sugar and whipping cream.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 7 minutes.
Stir, cook 7 more minutes.
Add butter and nuts.
Stir and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped up onion and green pepper. Drain fat. In another pan, cook macaroni and rinse with warm water. Mix ground beef, macaroni, tomatoes and kidney beans in one pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cook on medium heat about 30 minutes. Great with crackers or French bread.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Beat eggs, then blend in sugar and cracker crumbs.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. When cool, top with 1 can of blueberry pie filling and spread Cool Whip on top.

title: pink goop
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini about 1/4-inch thick.
Add water to cream of chicken soup.
Then mix zucchini, chicken soup, sour cream and shredded carrots together; mix well.
Saute cornbread stuffing mix in margarine until moist.
(I make a small pan of cornbread and crumble that to use if not using the Stove Top mix.)
Layer the zucchini mixture and stuffing into baking dish (2 layers), ending with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ginger pear muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, soda and spices. In mixing bowl, beat together brown sugar, yogurt, oil, egg and molasses.
Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Fold in pears, raisins and walnuts if desired.
Pour into buttered muffin tins and bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes 12 to 14.

title: zucchini cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a large skillet, saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add zucchini, cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly.
Add rice, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and egg; mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
In a small bowl, combine crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: low-fat steak salad
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and cook onion 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Toss greens, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Top with steak and onions.
Serve with Creamy Buttermilk Dressing.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, honey and peanut butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in granola.
Press into buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sour cream and cake mix.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased and floured sheet pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over batter.
Pour remaining batter over this.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: marinated salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli and cauliflower florets with mushrooms, tomatoes, olives, water chestnuts and onion.
Prepare dressing mix according to package directions using wine vinegar, water and oil. Pour dressing over vegetables.
Cover and marinate at least 8 hours.
Toss well before serving.
Serves 16.

title: chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding, then add oil, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans until done.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter in blender.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients with fork and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Mix butter, Texas Pete and vinegar.
Dip chicken in the mixture.
Place wings in sheet cake pans.
Sprinkle Hidden Valley Ranch dressing over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish steak
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Brown in oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: fantastic cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together and beat well.
This will make 2 pies.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine flour and brown sugar.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Stir 1 minute more and remove from heat.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to saucepan.
Bring to gentle boil and cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: sunshine mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Cool and add lemon and pineapple juice.
Chill until jelly-like consistency.
Beat in softened sherbet.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Place in mold in refrigerator.
Unmold to serve.

title: quick potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a long baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup whipped topping in bowl.
Spread in prepared dish.
Prepare vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes individually using package directions reducing milk to 1 1/2 cups each.
Layer puddings over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining 3 cups whipped topping.
Chill, covered, until serving time.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Add sugar and spices to the chopped apples; let stand a few hours.
Blend oil and unbeaten egg in apple mixture.
Blend flour, baking soda and baking powder and mix together, stirring until blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels, then crumble. Mix bacon, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Place mixture on cocktail rye bread.
Heat until cheese is bubbly at 350°.
Yields about 20 appetizers.

title: clam-cream dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce in a medium size bowl; stir in clams.
Chill.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Drain all canned beans except pork and beans.
Brown beef and drain.
Cook onions and bacon together; drain.
Mix all in crock-pot on low for 4 to 9 hours.

title: nut fingers
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, water and vanilla, then nuts.
Roll into two inch bars.
Bake at 350° 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly, then roll in additional confectioners sugar.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar and pat it flat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake this "pretzel" crust at 350° for 7 minutes. Beat cream cheese, then mix sugar into it.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spread mixture over pretzel crust (make sure crust is hot or it will pull up out of pan).
Refrigerate while doing next step.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour 3/4 cup of sugar over peaches and let sit.
Melt oleo in a large baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Mix batter of 3/4 cup of sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter into melted oleo. Pour peaches into batter; don't stir!
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer ingredients as listed in shallow dish.
Serve hot or cold with Tostitos or Fritos king size corn chips.
Yum!

title: rosy raspberry fizz
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream soda in large mixing bowl. Beat until blended.
Slowly pour in cream soda, mixing with up and down motion.
Serve immediately in tall glasses.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet until set (about 1 minute).
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: great popsicles
directions: Dissolve gelatin, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Freeze in popsicle holders, ice trays or small paper cups.

title: parmesan bread fingers
directions: Combine biscuit
mix,
yeast and salt in bowl.
Stir in water until mixture clings to itself.
Turn dough onto floured surface. Knead 8 to
times.
Roll
out
into
a
13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangle.
Brush half
of
butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place
dough in pan, pressing to fit.
Cut crosswise into 16
strips,
then
lengthwise
in half.
Brush with remaining butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let rise 15 minutes. Bake at
for 15 minutes.
Turn off oven; allow sticks to remain in oven 15 minutes.
Makes 32 bread fingers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer.
When ready to serve, pour into casserole dish.
Warm thoroughly.
Add cheese and let melt. Remove from oven.
Top with crumbled taco chips, diced tomato and shredded lettuce.
Use taco sauce, if desired.

title: sinful trash
directions: Put white almond bark in microwave for about 2 minutes. Mix the other ingredients in large bowl. Pour white almond over mixture and spoon out on wax paper until dry.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat egg; add milk and stir in Bisquick and cheese.
Beat all this until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and slice.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Put 1/4 cup of nuts in with other ingredients and mix well. Form into ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir together soup and wine; spoon evenly over chicken.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over chicken.
Drizzle with the melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter chocolate surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Place a Hershey's Kiss in the center of each cookie ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar; add egg.
Mix well. Combine flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to butter mixture. Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla; mix well.
Press 2 thirds of dough in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with preserves. Crumble rest of dough on top.
Bake until brown at 350°, for 30 minutes.

title: turkey cutlet saute
directions: Prepare frozen vegetables according to package directions. Meanwhile, sprinkle turkey cutlets with salt and pepper.
In 12-inch skillet over medium high heat, heat oil.
Add cutlets and cook for 4 to 6 minutes until cooked through turning once.
Using tongs, remove to serving platter and keep warm.
In blender, process roasted red peppers with their liquid until smooth.
Add to drippings in skillet along with water.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes stirring frequently until hot.
Toss vegetables with chopped parsley and spoon onto platter with turkey.
Serve garnished with parsley sprigs and red pepper sauce.
Serves 4.

title: aunt myrt's sheath cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into mixing bowl.
Put next 4 ingredients into saucepan and heat.
Bring to boil and pour slowly over sugar and flour; mix well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.
Pour icing on cake while still hot.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, tapioca and jello.
Mix well and set aside while preparing the crust.
Line pie plate with your favorite crust.
Fill with rhubarb filling.
Sprinkle the crushed pineapple over the filling.
Adjust top crust and seal. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cube and brown chicken in a large skillet.
Add chopped onion. Slowly add spaghetti sauce and water.
Blend in Minute rice. Bring to a boil.
Cover until rice is tender.
Serve with garden salad and toasted garlic bread.

title: chicken-zucchini bake
directions: Arrange zucchini (or broccoli) in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, milk and nutmeg.
Spread over chicken.
Combine Bisquick, cheese and egg.
Sprinkle over soup. Top with parsley and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Bring the 7-Up to a boil in a saucepan.
Take off heat and pour in the Jell-O, stirring to dissolve.
When thoroughly dissolved, stir in and mix the applesauce.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing. Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover with a tight lid. Leave overnight. Stir and sprinkle sunflower meats and almonds before serving.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Place in a cooker and cook until tender, salt to taste.
Let drain 1 hour after removing from heat.
Make juice and let set for 24 hours over the cabbage.
You can put in jars and cold pack for 20 minutes, enough to seal lids or you can put in plastic containers while cold and keep in the refrigerator for months.

title: chick-n-cue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients, except chickens.
This goes well with grilling.
Just keep brushing on chickens as they cook.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pie shell and bake; cool.
Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
When fluffy, add melted chocolate.
Add eggs one at a time, beating at least 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fruit slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add orange juice concentrate, stirring until orange juice is dissolved.
Add fruit.
Stir in soda.
Freeze in large container or several small ones.
Thaw in refrigerator about 1 hour or until slushy before serving.

title: braised venison
directions: Cover steaks with flour and sear on all sides in shortening. Place steaks in ovenproof dish. Add enough water to cover the bottom of the dish. Add 1 tablespoon vinegar. Cover tightly and cook very slowly in 300° oven about 2 hours, adding a little more liquid as necessary. About 30 minutes before meat is tender, add celery, apple, carrot and onion.

title: arctic melon pops
directions: In blender combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 8 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Cover with foil; make small knife cut.
Insert popsicle stick.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours. Peel off paper and eat.

title: tony's stuffed clams
directions: Clean clams by soaking in water and cornmeal for about 4 to 6 hours, stirring clams every hour.
Drain and soak in fresh water for about 1 hour.
Melt butter and combine bread crumbs, walnuts and finely chopped garlic.
Halve clams and stuff with mixture. Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until tops are lightly browned.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix together flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, salt and white sugar. Stir in milk and melted shortening.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Over entire mixture, pour hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend together first five ingredients.
Add oil and seed. Blend 2 minutes.

title: polish sausage, red beans and rice
directions: Place all ingredients except sausage and rice in a 2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage to beans the last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Serve 1 cup kidney bean mixture over 1 cup rice.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate several hours before serving to allow flavors to blend together.
Luscious served with raw celery, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli or green peppers.

title: fruit cup jelly
directions: Make according to package procedure on Sure-Jell box.

title: barbecued pork shoulder
directions: Place roast in large Dutch oven.
Add salted water to cover roast.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until pork is tender.
Drain and slice thin.
Place pork in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a large pot, bring the chicken stock and water to boil. Add all the other ingredients at once.
Bring the soup to boil and allow it to continue boiling for 15 minutes.
Then simmer it over low heat for at least 30 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and chocolate; add eggs.
Sift flour and soda together; add to chocolate mixture.
Add Coca-Cola.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: linguine with red clam sauce
directions: In a wide, heavy skillet (preferably nonstick), saute minced garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes with their juice and break them up with a wooden spatula.
Add juice from clams and anchovy paste, red pepper and oregano.
Simmer until sauce is thickened and oil floats free.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° until firm.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients and put in casserole.
Cover with crackers, melt margarine and dribble over crackers.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Put half the crumbs in a 9-inch pie pan.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together peanut butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Form into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper until dry.

title: breakfast and brunch casserole
directions: Cut up bacon and fry until crisp; drain.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Add milk and soup, then bread, bacon and cheese. Grease baking dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight, unbaked. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add the beets and cook until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tofu and corn stir-fry
directions: Cut bell pepper in thin slivers.
Cut green onions diagonally. Slice mushrooms.
Drain and cut tofu in cubes.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil.
