Add corn and bell pepper; stir-fry 4 minutes. Add snow peas, green onions, mushrooms, tofu and garlic and stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, chicken and taco seasoning.
Set aside. Spread beans on round pizza pan.
Spoon chicken mixture on top of beans. Layer the following:
salsa, olives, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve cold with tortilla chips, or you can heat and serve.

title: wine jelly
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water until softened.
Stir in boiling water until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice and peel.
Mix and let cool.
Add wine and cognac.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart mold. Chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Unmold on chilled dessert platter.
Serve on pound cake or sponge cake.
Top with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern style beef stew
directions: Cut your stew beef into 1 to 2 inch size and toss in the mixture of flour and white pepper.
Cut potatoes and onions into 1 inch size.
Cut carrots up.
Put all of the ingredients into a slow cooker.
Add water and cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours. When you get ready to serve, turn the slow cooker up to high.
Mix the cornstarch and water together.
Add a little of the hot broth from the pot to the mixture, then add this mixture to the slow cooker.
Let cook until it thickens.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and nuts and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place 1 wafer in the bottom of each liner.
Mix the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into foil liners over the wafer 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Top with fruit.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix the cookie crumbs and oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with the next 3 ingredients.
Save a few crumbs for the top. Put in the freeze for about 8 hours.
Serve frozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Cook macaroni according to box directions.
Peel zucchini and slice into 1-inch cubes or slices.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Melt margarine in rectangular pan, 13 X 9 X 2, in oven.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chichen with flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake about 30 minutes longer.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add water, if necessary.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted rolls or bread.

title: chicken with angel hair pasta
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in olive oil, then bread crumbs.
Put garlic and seasonings on top of chicken.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray (Pam).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Boil pasta.
Serve chicken with pasta and sauce and a salad.

title: smothered steak
directions: Season steaks with salt, pepper and garlic and brown on both sides (5 to 10 minutes) in 1 teaspoon oil. In separate pan, heat beef broth and add flour and water mixture. Stir and let thicken. If you need it to be thickened more, add additional flour to mixture and stir with a fork. Be careful and add additional flour slowly or it will be lumpy. Add sliced onions and pepper to taste. Beef broth is salty so be careful about adding additional salt. Add gravy to steaks and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine oleo, sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: all-in-one breakfast
directions: Put rolls in bottom of greased pan.
Beat eggs and pour over rolls.
Crumble in sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets and reserve liquid.
Melt butter and blend in cornstarch.
Add beet juice and cook.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add sugar, vinegar, onion juice, salt, pepper and beets. Cook slowly until beets are heated through.
Prepare ahead and reheat before serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: hearty beef soup
directions: In a 4-quart glass bowl, combine beef and cook in microwave on Roast for 6 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once during cooking.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Cover; cook on Roast for 30 minutes or long enough for flavors to combine. Add macaroni during last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Completely cover chicken with water and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Debone chicken.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Turn out on board and knead until stiff.
Roll out very thin and allow to dry for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into strips and drop in broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine (chop margarine with a fork). Add oil and oranges.
Mix with mixer until blended.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in 3 greased and floured layer cake pans. Let cool.

title: creamy tex-mex pork chops
directions: Season each pork chop with salt, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon Tex-Mex seasoning. Turn chops over and season again. Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add pork chops to pan. Cook pork chops approximately 2 1/2 to 3 minutes per side, depending on thickness. Remove from pan. Add cream and salsa to pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon sauce over pork chops.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon. Mix together the mayo, sugar and vinegar and pour over salad. Mix well and chill.

title: mandarin spinach with poppy seed dressing
directions: For Dressing:
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt in blender or processor and mix well.
Add lemon juice with machine running; gradually add oil.
Stir in poppy seed.
Combine next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour dressing over salad; toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Mash and cream with butter, salt and canned milk.
Smooth potatoes on bottom of greased casserole pan.
Brown hamburger.
Season.
Drain any grease.
Add to casserole, topping potatoes.
Grate cheese and cover casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-way cookies
directions: Melt margarine onto a large cookie sheet.
Add the graham cracker crumbs.
Put on top of them the chocolate chips and the butterscotch chips.
Add the coconut.
Pour onto this the milk. Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reese's cup pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Blend Cool Whip and Reese's.
Pour into graham cracker crust and garnish with last 2 Reese's. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 400° oven
for 1 hour.
Cut in halves, lengthwise.
Remove from peelings
and mix with other ingredients except cheese.
Before
mixing,
saute
onions
in	bacon drippings.	Spoon mix into	potato	shells.
Top
with
grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: italian meatball spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, garlic, onion and bell pepper in olive oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, Italian style spaghetti mix, mushrooms, water, sugar, oregano, basil and bay leaf. Simmer.

title: cajun potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water and Cajun seasoning. Drain and separate on plate to let cool before mixing with egg mixture. This way the potatoes won't get too mushy. Sprinkle with a little salt while cooling.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix in order given and add blueberries last.
Put in pan and add topping.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir 1 cup boiling water into gelatin. Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.

title: low-fat peach pound cake
directions: Spray 10-inch tube pan with Pam.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Combine oil, yogurt and gradually add remaining sugar, beating well.
Add whole eggs and whites, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to yogurt mixture.
Beat well.
Dredge peaches with remaining 1/4 cup flour. Fold peaches into batter.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pan and cool.

title: raspberry basil dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients at high speed until completely blended.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and flour.
Add milk, margarine, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
It will have a crust so you don't have to make one.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Coat cucumber slices well.
Keep cool until served.

title: baked acorn squash filled with green peas
directions: I use this on Thanksgiving and serve around the turkey.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef in bottom of shallow pan (or casserole). Add bacon and chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over meats. Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Increase heat to 350° and bake for another 20 to 30 minutes, basting often.
Good served over rice.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Mix together the cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt, pepper, grated cheese and black olives.
Blend in the cooked macaroni.
Bake in greased casserole dish uncovered until brown and bubbly, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt cream cheese, soup, mayonnaise and onion. Add drained can of Veg-All and corn.
Mix together and pour into a greased glass baking dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle this mixture on top and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 1 pound coffee cans or loaf pans.
Fill coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour.

title: miracle cherry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan pudding, sugar, lemon juice and water. Add cherries with juice.
Cook and stir to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and food coloring.
Chill in baked 8-inch pie shell.
Top with whipped topping.

title: peanutty raisin fun balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together peanut butter, honey and 1/4 cup of the peanuts.
Add apple juice and Kellogg's Raisin Bran cereal, stirring until well combined.
Portion mixture, using level measuring-tablespoon.
Shape into balls.
Roll in remaining chopped peanuts.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve chilled.
Yield:
25 to 30 snacks.

title: mom's sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Resift twice with baking soda. Set aside.

title: barbecued venison ribs
directions: Prepare 1 part vinegar to 3 parts water, enough to cover the ribs.
Add some salt, bay leaves, peppercorns and onion.
Soak ribs in this for 2 days.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon salt, chili sauce, 1 cup water, steak sauce, chili powder and garlic powder; bring to a boil.
Brush the ribs with this sauce and baste them every 10 to 15 minutes during grilling.

title: hot spice cocktail
directions: Put pineapple, cranberry and water in large coffee pot.
In basket of coffee pot, put cinnamon sticks broken in 1/2, cloves and sugars.
Perk.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Cold boiled rice, oatmeal or potatoes.
Mix half and half with flour, salt and cold water in which rice, oatmeal or potatoes had been cooked.
Make thick paste and bake or fry.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine the apples, oranges,
pineapple and grapes in a large bowl; set aside.
Cook the eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, mustard and salt
in
a
saucepan
over
medium heat, stirring. When the sauce is thick, remove from heat and cool. Add the whipped cream.
Blend well,
then add the sauce to the fruit.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: pop nichols' coffee cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and vanilla for 10 minutes at medium speed.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts and add 1/2 of this mixture to cake mixture while mixing.
Put in an oblong cake pan. Cut the remaining 1/2 of this mixture into the cake after it is in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza(from amber's kindergarten recipe)
directions: Chop all veggies and put into a large bowl.
Halve the avocados, remove the pit and scoop out flesh and put in bowl with the veggies.
Add the salsa, lime juice and garlic.
Use a potato masher and a spatula to mix the contents of the bowl.
Mix until the guacamole is a consistent texure.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in deep fat until crisp.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and ice cream.
This can be stored in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add powdered milk; mix well.
Add extracts and Sweet 'N Low.
Spoon drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove from sheet and dust with cinnamon. Yield:
about 2 dozen (32 calories each).

title: veal with mushrooms
directions: Bread and fry cutlets in small amount of oil.
Remove and cool.
In saucepan, saute mushrooms in butter and parsley.
Add sour cream and soup, heating through.

title: lemon punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Chill or serve slushy.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Serves 25 to 30.
Great for weddings and showers.

title: yogurt-granola fruit medley
directions: Layer half of banana slices in a 1-quart bowl.
Lightly spread 1/4 of granola.
Arrange half of grapes over granola; spread with 1/4 of yogurt and sprinkle with 1/4 of granola.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill up to 3 hours.

title: nel's sandies
directions: Cream ingredients together and chill dough.
Shape cookies into crescent shapes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crisp as ice cucumber slices
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced vegetables; mix. Empty a tray of ice cubes in center of vegetables. Let stand 3 hours.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Combine and cook slowly until onion and pepper are done.
Grind beef or pork when done.
Combine meat and sauce.
Mix well.
Serve on barbecue buns with or without a slice of tomato.

title: pastor's delight
directions: Combine
all the ingredients at one time, stirring in a lot of love and determination.
Stay on your knees as long as it takes to assure that you're done.
If any doubts, remain in that same position.

title: chili (hot)
directions: On medium heat, saute onions and green pepper in oil, while adding ground beef.
Cook until all beef is brown.
Add chili powder, jalapeno peppers and crushed red pepper.
Stir to mix. Cook 3 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes, kidney beans and tomato paste.
Cook to boiling, then reduce heat to low and cook 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti, or with saltines.

title: spiced fruit salad(serves 6)
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add measured juice. Measure 2 1/4 cups and refrigerate until it starts to thicken. Blend remaining Jell-O slowly with mixer into cream cheese and cinnamon until smooth; set aside.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, zucchini and celery in olive oil.
Stir in tomatoes, carrots, parsley and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
Layer 1/4 sauce, 3 noodles, 1/3 Ricotta, 1/4 Mozzarella, 1/4 Parmesan, repeating three times.
Last layer, put sauce on top of noodles, then Mozzarella and Parmesan (no Ricotta on this layer).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 9 servings.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Thaw and then squeeze spinach to remove moisture.
Rinse, drain and pat dry the artichoke hearts.
Put Romano cheese in food processor with metal blade. Turn motor on and drop garlic through food tube to mince.
Stop motor and add spinach, artichokes, cream cheese and eggs.
Process until blended.
Put mixture in medium bowl and gently stir in mozzarella cheese.
Transfer to ovenproof baking dish and bake 20 - 25 minutes.

title: baked noodles
directions: Cook meat in butter, stirring with a fork, until meat turns grey.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add minced garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water about 8 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Add chopped scallions, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Mix all ingredients; heat in oven.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed and pour over mixture.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese, butter and milk.
Pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugars and water.
Add peanuts; cook to 300° on candy thermometer.
At 300°, remove from heat and add butter and soda.
Stir well.
Pour onto greased surface.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Wash and destem mushrooms.
Add onion mixture to sausage and mash together.
Form into balls and stuff into caps.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sausage will pull away from caps.
Serves 20.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter and brown sugar.
Put in the bottom of a Bundt pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Melt 1/2 cup butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Coat frozen rolls with this mixture.
Arrange rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with instant pudding, cover with damp cloth and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes and turn out.
Yields 24.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, egg and sugar.
Add soda, flour and salt.
Add vinegar and vanilla and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken breasts
directions: For sauce, combine all ingredients and salt to taste.

title: almond joy cookies
directions: Mix condensed milk and unsweetened milk in top of double boiler for 7 minutes.
Add cooked mixture with coconut, vanilla and salt. Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Place almonds on top of each cookie, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Watch as it gets real brown on bottom.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients except corn and soda 5 minutes, mixing well and stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir in quickly.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Put in two large flat pans and place in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring two or three times.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Mix together Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, garlic salt, pepper, onion salt and liquid smoke.
Place beef or venison in the mixture and soak for 1/2 hour.
Remove and bake in slow oven until dry.

title: dad's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Mix all other ingredients together. Return to stove and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put on hot dogs and enjoy!

title: miss clara meek's chess pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Mix in flour, vinegar, milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat filling until creamy.
Mix cake batter.
Grease edged cookie sheet with Pam spray.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper and grease wax paper with Pam spray.
Pour cake batter on wax paper. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Dust one side of a tea towel well with 10x sugar.
Put cake on the dusted tea towel and roll up cake in tea towel until cold.
Unroll and put filling on cake. Roll up cake again onto foil and wrap cake up with foil.

title: baked beans with ground meat
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good!

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans, cherries and cut up dates.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set.
Makes 7 dozen.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blender salsa
directions: Wash and cut vegetables into chunks.
Include pepper seeds. Add everything to blender except 2nd bell pepper.
Taste for hotness.
If milder salsa is wanted, add 2nd bell pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Keep in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Serve with chips.
Can be frozen for longer storage.

title: puerto rican broth
directions: Make a broth with the chicken innards.
Cut the chicken in 4 pieces and season it with the garlic and tart orange.
Boil the oil and deep fry the chicken.
Add the chopped onion, hot pepper, tomato soup, can of peppers with the liquid, the liquid of the petit pois, salt, black pepper, dry wine and water.
Wash and drain the rice.
When the chicken is almost done, add the rice.
Keep it on low heat until the rice is cooked.
When ready to serve, add the petit pois and the cheese.
Mix it together.
Decorate with the peppers.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.

title: fruited rice
directions: In a saucepan, combine uncooked rice with chicken broth and apple juice; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook for 20 to 25 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add apples; saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in raisins and onions; saute 3 more minutes.
Add rice to skillet and toss.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: carameled walnuts
directions: Combine sugars and sour cream and cook until boiling (236°). Add vanilla and stir until thickens.
Add walnuts; stir until coated.
Spread on cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Mix together and pour over second layer.
Use remaining Cool Whip; spread on top.
Shred some chocolate and put on top with nuts.
This is good if you freeze it.
Take out about 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Mix together and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over high heat for 7 minutes.
Brown sausage; pour off grease, reserving 2 tablespoons in saucepan. Add green pepper, celery and onion to meat and cook until onion is shiny.
Add to rice mixture.
Add mushroom soup to rice and mix well.
Top with slivered almonds and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat balls for spaghetti
directions: Soak bread in water for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add eggs; mix well. Mix with ground beef and the rest of the ingredients.
With wet hands, form mixture into small balls (about 24).
Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil.
Drain oil and add to spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour loosely covered.
Serves 8.

title: "done buttered" biscuits
directions: Mix together and fill muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 regular size muffins, but 36 miniatures, and are much better in small size!

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Make small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
May freeze before; if so, bake longer.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, sugar, cocoa, milk and shortening.
Spread in a 9 x 9 pan, then sprinkle with a mixture of the brown sugar and cocoa.
Cover all with the boiling water (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish. Put a single layer of graham crackers on bottom. Combine instant pudding and milk and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Put a layer of pudding mix over graham crackers. Repeat this process 2 more times.

title: cole slaw #2
directions: In large bowl, combine 1st 4 ingredients.
Add shredded vegetables.
Mix well, cover and chill.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter, mixing well.
Line 1 3/4-inch muffin pans with miniature paper liners.
Spoon 1 teaspoon graham cracker mixture into each liner; gently press into bottom.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add extract.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add salt and baking powder to flour.
Add this mixture alternately with milk and beat well. Turn into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Seed and cut grapes in half and add with remaining ingredients.
Chill. Whip cream and add just before serving.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and butter to boiling.
Remove from heat. Add condensed milk.
Will keep in fridge.

title: apple munch bread
directions: Mix the eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Mixture is thick. Add the apples, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° in 2 large loaf pans or Bundt pan for 1 hour or more. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting, if desired.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add sugars, butter, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares after cooling.

title: pear velvet salad
directions: Strain pears and bring juice to boil.
Dissolve jello in pear juice.
Combine pears, cheese and 4 tablespoons jello mixture in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining jello mixture and blend again.
Refrigerate until soft-set and fold in Cool Whip. Chill several hours before serving.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, then beat Bisquick and oil with eggs on slow speed of mixer until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, adding zucchini last and stir with spoon until all are mixed.
Spread in pan and bake 30 minutes or until moistened and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: carrot ring
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mix margarine until soft (do not overbeat).
Add brown sugar and blend.
Add eggs, then carrots. Beat in flour that has been sifted with salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add lemon juice and water; don't overbeat.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan for 1 hour.
Pan should be well-greased and floured.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl. Mix 1 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour in pans.
Bake oblong 40 to 45 minutes, round pans 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters. Put cover on and shake. Pour 1/2 of butter in bottom of Bundt pan. Pour rest of margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in 9-inch round cake pan. Simmer until sugar melts.
Remove from heat.
Add syrup and nuts and stir.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and place in pan containing brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Use powdered sugar to dip hand into as you roll balls.

title: no-cook fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large saucepan and melt.
Then mix powdered sugar, cocoa and salt into the mixture.
Mix until smooth as possible.
Pour into greased 9 x 17-inch pan.
Very good and you can't taste the cheese.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar; blend well.

title: poppin party mix
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
Pour butter over cereal mix, mixing well.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion powder; toss well to coat.
Spread into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally during baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix the two soups with 1 cup broth and pour over chicken. Melt butter.
Mix with stuffing mix and 1 cup broth.
Pour this on top.
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare and cut potatoes in quarters.
Shake potatoes in a big bag containing flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and add potatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, turning once.

title: linguini al pesto
directions: Saute garlic in butter and margarine until
lightly golden; add basil and parsley and cook one minute; add pine nuts.
Cook linguini as directed on package.
Drain well; serve linguini on large serving dish topped with pesto sauce and fresh ground pepper.
Grated cheese (Parmesan) may be sprinkled on top.

title: amy's cheese & spinach pinwheels
directions: Stir together all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread about 1/2 c. mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up tightly, wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
To serve, unwrap and cut each into 10 slices.
Makes 5 dozen pinwheels.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit, mix with Cool Whip, coconut and marshmallows and refrigerate.
This is light and refreshing.
Great with Thanksgiving dessert, buffets or parties.

title: banana fritters
directions: Combine rum, brandy, lime juice, lime peel, sugar and molasses.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Marinate bananas in mixture for 1 hour.
Drain and dry well.

title: cape cod mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash well.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese, onion, margarine, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Place in casserole. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, checking after 45 minutes.

title: survival chili
directions: In a large pot, heat oil until hot.
Add half of the meat; brown well on all sides.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add remaining meat and brown.
Return all meat to pot.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally and adding more water if needed, for 3 hours.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush 3/4 box vanilla wafers; pour melted oleo over.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Use rest of wafers to go around sides of pan. Mix cream cheese, milk and lemon juice with mixer until smooth and spread on crust.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple over filling.
Place sliced bananas over this.
Cover with Cool Whip. Decorate with pecans and cherries.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl except Stove Top and butter
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° or until set. Saute Stove Top in butter until browned.
Spread over casserole and bake 5 minutes.

title: orange pecans
directions: Bring 1st three ingredients to a boil, then add all the pecans; stir with all the pecans, until they are coated and the mixture is absorbed.
Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: harvest vegetable pie
directions: Steam broccoli until almost tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Chop broccoli; add onion and cheese.
Fold together lightly.
Arrange in a greased 10-inch pie pan.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, Bisquick mix, salt and pepper together with wire whip for 1 minute.
Pour egg mixture over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Topping:
In small bowl, cream 2/3 cup dry cake mix, brown sugar and pecans.
Cut in butter and set aside.

title: easy shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp and drain.
Boil noodles and drain. Chop onion. Mix all remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: special bars
directions: Mix first 3 items and put "half" in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt about 50 Kraft caramels in the evaporated milk.
After cake is baked, sprinkle chocolate chips over cake and dribble the caramel mix over the chocolate chips.
Then crumble the remaining half of the cake mixture on the very top of the cake.
Bake again for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage on rye
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck together.
Drain.
Add cheese, sauce and oregano.
When cheese is melted, cool slightly.
Place meat mixture on party rye.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes, until mixture bubbles.
This can be frozen in layers and put into oven frozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300° in large tube pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake by directions on box.
In a punch bowl, crumble 1/2 of the cake, then on top of cake, put 1/2 of pineapple, cherry and blueberry filling.
Add 1 container of Cool Whip.
Repeat with other half of ingredients.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain. Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, peppers and tomato sauce. Pour into 2-quart casserole. In a separate bowl, prepare corn bread mix according to package and add 1/2 the onions. Spoon muffin mixture around outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions. Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: lemon-poppy seed bread
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 4 minutes with electric beater. Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick.
Yield: 2 large loaves or 3 nut-loaf size pans.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Put as much as desired in 1 cup of hot water.
Enjoy.

title: pineapple-nut dip
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar until thick, then cool. Mix other ingredients with pineapple. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttercream frosting(makes about 3 cups)
directions: Cream butter until soft in medium size bowl; add sugar gradually, alternating with cream, blending well after each addition.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Take out 1 1/2 cups for white frosting; tint remaining pale pink with red food coloring.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Let yeast dissolve in water and set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients as listed together.
Cut shortening into dry mixture as you do for pie dough.
Stir in the buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Thoroughly blend.
The dough can be refrigerated or can be kneaded lightly.
After removing the dough from the refrigerator, it should be allowed to sit at room temperature to allow it to rise.
Roll out on floured board and cut biscuits with biscuit cutter.
Place in a greased pan and allow the dough to rise a little before baking.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Dough can be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add green food coloring.
Stir in cornflakes.
Immediately drop by spoonful onto waxed paper or Teflon pan.
Decorate with red candies at once to make stick. Nice for Christmas.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Mix everything but Tater Tots. Put into a greased baking dish.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Mix sugar, shortening,
milk, eggs, salt, lemon oil and ammonia.
Add flour until stiff.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out until it is 1/4 inch thick on floured board.
Cut as desired and poke with fork.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes.
Store in covered containers.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil 2 cups water; remove from heat and drop in tea bags. Cool to room temperature.
Boil 6 cups water with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
After all ingredients are cooled, mix all with brandy, orange juice and lemonade.
Pour into a large container and freeze.
To serve, put 2 to 4 tablespoons of slush in a drink glass and fill with 7-Up or 50/50.
Deliciously refreshing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice and cook squash, onion, salt and butter until tender. Drain squash; add sour cream and soup.
Mix 1/2 butter or margarine to squash.
Spread other 1/2 over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle ham and cheese into pie shell.
Beat eggs lightly and stir in flour, milk and seasoning.
Pour mixture over ham and cheese.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Put butter, honey and milk in a large saucepan and heat until butter is melted.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to milk mixture.
Add flour a cup at a time and mix well.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Punch down and pat out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Add a pat of butter and fold over.
Put in greased cookie sheet or pan.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash(italian style)
directions: Heat olive
oil
in
a large skillet.
Grate garlic and chop celery
and
onions.
Add this to heated olive oil.
Cook until brown, then blend tomatoes in blender and put in a large pot.
Add garlic,
onions
and celery.
Quarter mushrooms and add to sauce,
also
add tomato paste.
Cook ground chuck and pork. Drain
fat	and
add
to
sauce.
Add
red wine, sugar, oregano and sweet
basil.
Bring
to a boil, then simmer for 3 to 4 hours,
stirring occasionally.
When finished, pour over spaghetti or elbow macaroni.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix half of sugar with flour.
Add half of milk, then mix in rest of sugar and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: honey tea ring
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Prepare baking mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits.
On surface, lightly floured with baking mix, roll out dough to 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and raisins.
Roll up, starting on long side.
Seal long edge.

title: short ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Arrange beef ribs in Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and bake about 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in a large black skillet.
Add sugar, egg and dates. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Shape into balls while still hot and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Spread on top 1 cup grated cheese and 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled raisin cake(jesus cake)
directions: Combine raisins, shortening and 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling point; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg in a medium size bowl.
Beat in remaining 1/2 cup water and cooled raisin liquid.
Mix in dry ingredients gradually; beat until smooth.
Stir in cooled raisin mixture.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, salt and sugar).
Add to eggs. Add syrup, melted butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Place pecans in bottom of pie crusts.
Pour filling over pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 pecan pies.

title: jello cake
directions: Put in a cup, one package of Jell-O and 3/4 cup boiling water. Stir and then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix and set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add flour.
Blend together at high speed.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.

title: treats
directions: Microwave:
Melt margarine in a 4-quart microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows, mix to coat.
Heat 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Add cereal, mix to coat. Press firmly into greased foil-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Turn onto cutting surface, peel off foil and cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve cold.

title: mrs. fisher's crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300° or 325°.
Melt shortening.
Add sugars and flour with cinnamon.
Mix together, then take out 1/2 cup to use for topping.
Add nuts to first mixture; add well-beaten eggs. Put soda in buttermilk and add to rest of mixture.
Mix all together.
This will be a little thin.
Pour in well-greased and floured pan (9 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle topping mixture over top of batter.
Bake 1 hour or until cake leaves sides of pan or springs back when touched.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 baked pie crusts.

title: amish apple butter
directions: Quarter and core apples.
Cook in cider until tender; force through sieve.
Cook pulp until thick; stir often to prevent sticking.
Cool about 30 minutes, then add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat for about 1 hour.
Put in jars, leaving 1/2-inch from top, seal, then put in a large kettle with rack and boiling water.
Process about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 half pints.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Place in large bowl in order given above. Cover lightly and store overnight or for several hours in refrigerator. Toss just before serving.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix onion, cheese and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: venison stew
directions: Cube venison and dredge in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil.
Cover and simmer while preparing vegetables.
Cut vegetables in bite size pieces.
Put meat and vegetables into large pot; add water to cover; add 1 bay leaf.
Cook until tender.
Add 1 package brown gravy mix and cook a few minutes longer.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat and stir in water.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
In salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, onion, green pepper, olives and cheese; toss.
Place lettuce mixture on individual salad plates.
Spoon on meat and top with corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, and powder; set aside.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Add rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, slice, boil and drain eggplant.
Mix the remaining ingredients together, then add the boiled eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flower garden cake
directions: Put together the gelatin and water to soak.
Cook the egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon juice until it coats a wooden spoon, then add gelatin mixture.
Add the egg whites and sugar to the rest.
Break the angel food cake into pieces.
Put the cake and sauce in layers into the angel food cake pan; refrigerate overnight.
Turn upside-down onto a plate to serve.

title: raised buttermilk biscuits
directions: Add yeast to buttermilk.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Alternately add dry ingredients and yeast milk, beating after each addition.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: morton's salad dressing
directions: Mix all together; store in quart jar in refrigerator until needed.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine the flour and salt.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk and stir until well blended.
Roll out dough to 1/2 inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 1 dozen biscuits.

title: red cinnamon cucumbers
directions: Add water to cover (4 to 6 quarts).
Drain.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to directions on package for 5 minutes.
Drain green beans and mix with remaining ingredients, but using only half of French fried onions in mixture.
Butter glass Corning dish and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour (uncovered).
Sprinkle remaining French fried onions on top after baking for 1/2 hour, then bake for additional 2 minutes.

title: ham-cheese quiche
directions: Combine meat, cheese and onion.
Place in pie shell (may prebake pie shell about 5 minutes if desired).
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and red pepper until frothy and pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, until set and golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
May be served with fruit salad or green salad.
Serves 4.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients and shape in 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: ricky's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla in a large bowl; blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set, covering outer edges with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 pans according to instructions.
Cool and then split in two to make 4 layers.

title: loaded baked potato soup
directions: Dice unpeeled red potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in a large dutch oven, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 min. or until 3/4 cooked.
In a separate large dutch oven, combine melted margarine and flour, mixing until smooth.
Place over low heat and gradually add Half and Half, stirring constantly. Continue to stir until smooth and liquid begins to thicken.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until creamy.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add hot water, soda and salt.
Then add the cocoa last.
After everything is mixed together, drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dill seed bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with warm water and dash of sugar.
Add cottage cheese, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, soda, egg, onion and dill seed. Mix all together, then add flour.
Let rise; punch down.
Put in greased loaf pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Form into loaf with strips of bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.
Serve hot or cold with mustard sauce.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add flour and mix well. Add broth, milk and seasonings.
Cook for 30 minutes on low heat, stirring often.
Add half and half and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk, cream cheese, vanilla and confectioners sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 3 graham cracker pie crust shells.
Freeze and serve frozen. Garnish with chocolate shavings or chocolate syrup.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and water to boil and add sugar and flour.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or larger for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost while still hot.

title: pig-n-basket
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onion, rice, salt and pepper in skillet.
Set aside.
Take core out of cabbage.
Put in boiling water and simmer until it will separate.
Trim veins and take leaves off, one at a time.
Spoon ground beef mixture into leaves, roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Wash sauerkraut to take out some of the strongness.
Put 1/2 in bottom of deep pan or crock-pot.
Put ham hocks in sides and put pigs in the middle. Cover with rest of kraut.
Add tomato soup and water.
Pour over all.
Let simmer slowly for 2 hours.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add cool whip and sour cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat
soup,
mayonnaise,
margarine, onions and cheese. Add other ingredients.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer crackers on top. Bake, covered, for
20 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine, oil and marshmallows.
Stir until mixed well.
Cool slightly and pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Add M&M's last.
Press into greased pan and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in 2 or 3 tablespoons butter.
When cool, put in blender.
Put broth and zucchini in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons Cream of Wheat. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake 2
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and crushed graham crackers and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, Crisco and salt until warm.
Stir constantly to melt Crisco.
Add dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Shape in rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together. Pour over cabbage and carrots. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hrs.

title: vietnam fried rice
directions: Heat in large skillet the cooking oil.
Add meat, garlic, onion, salt, sugar, pepper and soy sauce.
Stir-fry until meat is tender and hot, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add frozen peas.

title: blueberry ice cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Press half of ice cream in a layer in bottom of cooled pie shell.
Freeze.
Spread 1/2 can of filling over ice cream; re-freeze.
Cover with layer of ice cream.
Freeze and top with rest of filling.
Freeze.
Add cream of tartar and dash of salt to egg whites and beat.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time and beat.
Pile lightly on frozen pie and seal well at edge of crust.
Put pie in oven and bake 3 minutes to brown meringue. Freeze.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: aunt jane's cherry tarts
directions: Mix well.
Put mixture in tart papers 2/3 full.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Check after 25 minutes.
Cool.
Put spoonful of cherry pie filling on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown the turkey, cabbage, and onions.
Add enough soy sauce that the meat mixture will not burn.
When fully cooked, add peanut butter.
Wrap about 1 Tbsp. of meat mixture in egg roll wrap according to package instructions.
Deep fry at 370° until lightly browned.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain and mix together.

title: sirloin strips italiano
directions: Slice steaks into strips.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a heavy skillet with salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon seasoning.
Add pepper strips, sliced mushrooms and chopped onions.
Heat remaining oil in wok or skillet.
Saute steak strips for 5 minutes, stirring to cook evenly.
Add another tablespoon seasoning.
Add vegetable mixture with either a jar of chunky style spaghetti sauce or 1 can tomatoes and 1/2 can water.
Cook for about 1 hour.
Cook rice and salt according to directions on package.
Serve stir-fry over hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt oleo and pour over crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour part of crackers in baking dish; place chicken on crackers.
Mix soup, broth and sour cream; heat until all mixed good.
Pour over chicken.
Put rest of crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together sugar and cream cheese; pour over crust.
Layer strawberries, pineapple and bananas over cream cheese.
Cover with crushed pecans.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until mixed. Cover. Chill. Makes 3 cups.

title: hot dog cheesies(kid's recipe)
directions: Drop hot dogs into saucepan of boiling water.
Lower heat. Cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes. Drain.

title: crumb topping for fruit pies
directions: Mix sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit pie and spread evenly.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix with first mixture.
Place batter in greased pan. Dampen hand with water.
Press batter to all parts of pan.
Cook at 350°.
Turn out and cut into squares while hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add the grated zucchini; mix well.
Add all the dry ingredients, nuts and raisins; stir in last.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese and olive swirls
directions: Blend cheese, butter and Tabasco.
Stir in flour.
Gather into a ball.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.
Roll into 6 x 10-inch rectangle between two sheets of wax paper.
Remove top piece of wax paper and sprinkle dough with olives.
Beginning with long end, roll up "jelly roll style" and seal the edges.
Wrap in wax paper and twist ends.
Be sure dough is tightly rolled.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and bake 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 10 to 20 minutes until edges light brown.
Serve immediately.

title: alma's rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, turning off oven for the last 1/2 hour. Makes 3 loaves.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soup, water and rice.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pride of indiana cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Next mix in coconut and oats.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cousin pattie's life preserving muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased muffin tin. Sprinkle with brown sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: caramel  pie
directions: Mix in large saucepan 2 cups sugar, flour, butter, milk, salt and slightly beaten egg yolks. Place over medium heat and cook until slightly thickened. Place 1/2 cup of sugar in heavy skillet over medium heat until it has melted and is a bright brown color. When this stage is reached, add the first mixture to the skillet, stirring constantly; continue to cook until mixture is smooth, creamy and thick. Remove from heat. Pour into 2 (9-inch) baked pastry shells. Top with meringue and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter. Add beaten eggs and pecans. Mix thoroughly. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and complete baking for about 30 minutes.
Brush with butter while still hot.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to a rolling boil.
Add flour all at once
and heat until smooth and dough forms a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat vigorously after each addition until dough is smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes or until done.
Test by removing one puff from oven with a spatula.
If it doesn't fall it is done.

title: creamed turkey with biscuits
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; stir in flour.
Add hot broth gradually; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients; pour into flat casserole.
Cover with biscuits cut in small circles.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Place pecan halves in 6 groups of 3 in a ring in a buttered pie plate.
Top each group with a caramel.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until caramels are soft but not melted.
Turn dish a half turn halfway through cooking.
Microwave chocolate morsels (in bowl) on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until morsels are melted.
Stir occasionally.
Spread about 1/2 teaspoon of chocolate over each caramel.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Repeat.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onion in a 6-quart heavy saucepan.
When almost done, add mushrooms, including juice.
Add all other ingredients (add water to the consistency you prefer).
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti or other noodles.
Freezes well.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix together ground turkey, stove top stuffing, seasoning and all, 1 chopped onion and 1 egg.
Form into loaf.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 60 minutes until brown.

title: wiener schnitzel(german)
directions: Pound the cutlets very thin.
Dredge with flour.
Combine cheese, 2 tablespoons flour, egg, 1 teaspoon parsley, salt, pepper and milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Dip each floured cutlet into this mixture and then into the bread crumbs.
Cook in margarine over low heat until tender and brown.
Remove to serving dish.
Add lemon juice to pan juices and pour over cutlets.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Rinse chipped beef in cold water.
Chop or shred and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll each half of chicken breast and place on top of chipped beef.
Combine soup and sour cream; mix well.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours. Serves 6 -8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
all ingredients, saving some tomato sauce for top. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Stir together pineapple, sugar, flour and grated Cheddar cheese; set aside.
In second bowl, mix crushed crackers with melted margarine.
Pour pineapple mixture into greased baking dish.
Top with cracker topping.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix above and spread on rye bread.

title: golden rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly and smooth.

Stir in chicken broth and milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute and pour over the chicken, mushrooms and green pepper which have been put into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together oleo, cake mix and 1 beaten egg.
Spread in bottom of greased and floured cake pan.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 beaten eggs.
Pour over top of previous mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When cake is cooled, cut in small squares.
This is very rich.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Add sherry to white sauce and gently fold in crab meat.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: caramel-apple bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and shortening. Stir in 1 3/4 cups flour, the oats, salt and baking soda.
Remove 2 cups of the mixture; reserve.
Press remaining mixture in an ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: good to the last drop cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam Non Stick. Pour in batter.
Begin in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Mix all dry ingredients and sift into mixture. Add milk and flavoring.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325° in a prepared tube pan.
Use a Caramel Icing.

title: doggie chews
directions: Mix flour, drippings and oatmeal together.
Stir in water or milk in which bouillon cubes have been dissolved.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and pat down.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fresh vegetable pizza(in honor of "peter the great")
directions: Press crescent roll dough on large pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour hot water over shortening; add sugar and salt.
When cooled to lukewarm, add yeast.
Add about half
of
the flour, beating with a wire whisk or mixer until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add enough flour to form a dough stiff enough to shape.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Make
out
rolls in desired shape; brush with melted butter
and
let
rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° until desired brown.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Crumble up.
Put 1 cup mixture aside for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: schoodle bake
directions: Mix meat and pasta.
Add cottage cheese and egg.
Pour 1/2 Ragu into mixture; mix.
Put in a casserole dish.
Pour rest of Ragu over top; sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let set before serving.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: lemony barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make jello as regular and let set in refrigerator until done as usual.
Put Cool Whip, a little at a time, into jello, whipping it with mixer.
Add sliced strawberries to mixture.
Stir and spoon into pie shell.
Let set 1 hour.
Serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Place pecans on bottom of pie crust, unbaked.
Beat eggs lightly and
add
sugar,
Karo
syrup,
vanilla, salt and beat. Cream flour
and
butter
together then beat into Karo mixture. Pour over nuts.
Bake
at
425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° until done.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Refrigerate cucumbers, salt and onion overnight.
Next morning, drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar; mix well with cucumber and onion.
Allow to stand a few hours, then put in containers and freeze.
Enjoy this winter!

title: tex-mex
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Place Velveeta in a small bowl and microwave on 1/2 power for 5 minutes.
Stir halfway through. After cheese has melted, stir in meat and relish.
Serve in small crock-pot with chips.

title: chicken livers and vegetables
directions: Cut onions and green peppers in eighths.
Clean livers and season lightly.
Put livers in frying pan, hot with medium-high heat.
Cook livers 3 to 5 minutes, while stirring.
Take livers out and set on side.
Place all vegetables in pan and put top on pan.
Steam vegetables and stir occasionally for 3 to 5 minutes (enable asparagus to break apart).
Put livers back in pan with vegetables, mixing well.
Put cooking wine in and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces and towel drain.
Break cauliflower into flowerets and slice thin.
Dice onion.
Fry bacon until crisp and break in pieces.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Top with 1/2 chips.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour half of chips in batter and the other half on top.
Improves flavor if sits 1 day.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 cookie sheets, 15 1/2 x 12-inches; keep warm.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies into a 13 x 5 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix pudding as instructed on box and put pudding over the crushed Oreos.
Put Cool Whip over pudding and place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables, beans, celery and onion in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add grated cheese. Spread mayonnaise over this. Crush Ritz crackers and spread over the mayonnaise.
Melt butter and pour over top of crackers. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: healthy heart soup
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil. Add everything except pasta and cheese to sauteed vegetables. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add pasta and cook until done. Serve with grated cheese on top. Serves 6 main dish servings.

title: angel hair pasta with creamy mushroom sauce and fresh herbs
directions: Melt butter in a heavy medium saucepan over low heat.
Add shallots and cook 1 minute.
Add 1 3/4 cups cream and bring to a simmer; stir.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring often about every 30 minutes.
(Sauce can be kept covered up to 1 day in fridge.)
Cook pasta to a boil uncovered.
Drain and transfer to large serving bowl.
Add tarragon, chives and 2 tablespoons parsley to sauce.
Add sauce to pasta and toss until thoroughly coated.

title: marni's green gazpacho
directions: Coarsely chop half the zucchini and cucumber.
Also chop the peppers and onion; mince the garlic.
Make sure you chop everything quite small.
Place these ingredients in a bowl; toss with parsley, basil, olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice, Tabasco and a dash of salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: waffles
directions: Beat all ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Makes two 12-inch waffles.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, and heat.
Place chicken in broiler pan.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Place under broiler.
Broil for 40 to 50 minutes, turning every 10 minutes.

title: lime punch
directions: Use amounts according to servings needed.

title: crunchy cheeseroni
directions: Mix noodles, hamburger and the 2 soups together. Place 1/2 of the casserole mixture in a baking dish. The next layer is 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the fried onions. Next layer is the second 1/2 of the casserole mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onions and cheese on top and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: wyoming potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes (do not peel).
Cut into 8 pieces.
Place them in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cut bacon pieces (uncooked) and put on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle package of onion soup mix over top, then cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix sugar with peaches and put into unbaked crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until set in the middle.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Mix together all the prepared vegetables.
Put the chicken and oil in a thick skillet or wok.
Cook on a medium flame, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is 3/4 done.
Add the water, soy sauce and vegetables.
Reduce to a low to medium flame; cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Dissolve the cornstarch in water, then add to vegetables, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes; season with seasoned salt and garlic powder.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Then refrigerate overnight. Good with vegetable and chips.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg until smooth; add milk and melted shortening.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour this into flour and mix to a very soft dough. Drop by spoonfuls onto broiling broth
or slightly thickened stew. Cover tightly and cook 10 to 14 minutes depending on size of dumplings.

title: broccoli-cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add frozen broccoli.
Cover and steam until broccoli defrosts.
Add soup and milk.
Cook over medium heat until almost boiling.
Add half and half and heat to serving temperature.

title: boursin cheese ball
directions: Mix well first 8 ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in lemon pepper.
Best when a day or two old.

title: katie bars
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add other ingredients in layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: country bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs and oil.
Add 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 hour.
Punch down; cut in half.
Roll each half into 1 x 8 x 9-inch rectangle.
Roll dough from 9-inch side.
Place into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Brush with oil.
Let rise until about double (about 1 hour).
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Test for doneness by tapping top to sound hollow.
Remove from pans.

title: hot almond egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add salt and sugar; blend.
Add hot milk, almond flavoring and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into hot mixture.
Pour into cups.
Garnish with dollops of whipped cream and slivered almonds, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pepperoni and broccoli salad
directions: Wash and trim broccoli; use flowerets only.
Slice mushrooms. Drain artichokes.
Slice onion and separate into rings.
Slice pepperoni.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour dressing over and cover.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
This is a good make ahead salad.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour and cocoa.
Add nuts if desired.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend.
Mix with electric mixer two minutes. Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp over crackers
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add baking soda to soup.
Mix all in rice.
Add shrimp last.
Put this mixture over saltine crackers.

title: popcorn balls(that stay soft)
directions: Bring
butter, Karo and sugar to a hard boil.
Add Jell-O. Bring to a boil again.
Pour over popcorn and shape into balls or pack into angel food cake pan, well-greased.
Makes a nice attractive birthday cake.

title: cranberry-cream dessert salad
directions: Combine 1/2 package marshmallows with the pineapple. Break cream cheese in small pieces and mix with cream and remaining marshmallows.
Put both mixtures, covered, in refrigerator for several hours, overnight or until marshmallows are well softened. Force cranberries through medium blade of food chopper.
Wash orange, remove seed and white membrane in center (do not peel) and grind orange.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Beat marshmallow-cream mixture in electric mixer until consistency of whipped cream.
Fold in marshmallow-pineapple and cranberry mixtures and chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and coloring.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, then add vinegar and nuts.

title: north carolina bean salad
directions: Add everything together and toss.

title: hot crab teaser (or creamy hot crab dip)
directions: Puree the cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic in a food processor or blender until smooth. Transfer to a sauce pan or microwave safe bowl.
Stir in the crab meat, lemon juice, Old Bay seasoning, Worchestershire and red hot pepper sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, or heat in microwave until steaming hot. Spoon into a serving bowl, sprinkle with chopped scallions and serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti
directions: Meatball:
Take the water out of the bowl and put it on the stove.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put dressing in a bag.
Mix milk with soup.
Dip chicken in soup mixture then shake in bag of dressing.
Place in a pan.
Pour the rest of soup over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 90 minutes.

title: coconut washboards
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs. Add water and vanilla. Sift and add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix in coconut.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and pepper.
Add soups, water, mushrooms, garlic salt and oregano.
Heat.
Cook curly noodles; mix all together.
Put Parmesan cheese and 1 large Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 325°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves at least 12.

title: marie's louisiana rice
directions: Combine rice, carrots, onion and flour.
Blend soup, egg and seasonings and add to rice mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before turning out on a serving plate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: excellent cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans together in a bowl.
Beat with hand mixer until well mixed and creamy.
Form into a ball with your hands.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with any crackers.
Chill and refrigerate between servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
cocoa,
sugar,
flour
and
cornstarch; add melted margarine to this mixture, then add 6 eggs one at a time.
Add evaporated	milk,
coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 regular size crust or 2 deep dish pies.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Partially
freeze
beef; thinly slice across grain into bite size strips.
In wok, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add
half the beef and stir-fry until browned; remove.
Repeat with remaining
beef.
Stir-fry onions and green pepper until tender. Return
beef
to
wok.
Stir
in
undrained tomatoes, broth, paprika and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or	until
meat is tender.	Blend together sour cream and flour; gradually stir in about 1 cup hot mixture.	Return all to
wok. Cook
and stir until thickened and bubbly.	Cook and
stir	1 minute
longer.
Serve
over
noodles.
Makes
6 servings.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in one bowl.
In a second bowl, mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend the mixtures together.
Fold in apples and black walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured angel cake pan at 320° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables or chips.

title: rancho beans
directions: Do not drain beans.
Brown beef and onion flakes.
In a large casserole, put beans, ketchup, mustard, sugar and meat.
Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350° (uncovered).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and saute until clear.
Add broccoli; stir thoroughly several minutes.
Add soup.
Stir and simmer several minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add rice.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baba elgan's swedish pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer, adding water until runny thin.
In cast-iron skillet, add 1 teaspoon of oil.
Pour enough liquid to make a thin layer on bottom of skillet.
Cook until lightly brown on both sides.
Need oil for each addition.
Butter 1 side and pour on maple syrup. Roll up.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Measure dry ingredients.
Add butter, oil, eggs, milk and vanilla; blend well.
Fold in grated zucchini.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan one hour at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: congo cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar; cool.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut in baking bars when slightly cool.
Yields 3 dozen.
Don't over cook.

title: barb's broccoli salad
directions: Clean broccoli and blanch in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes. Rinse in cold water.
Drain.
In a large bowl mix broccoli, red onion rings and bacon pieces.
Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten. Sprinkle shredded cheese into salad (reserve some for top) and mix well.
Top with reserved cheese.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: canned apples(for future use)
directions: Let apples and sugar stand overnight.
Pack apples into quart jars tight and seal.
Put jars in cold water bath and bring to a boil.
Shut off the heat.
Let in about 1 hour.
These apples are very good used for pie, apple crisp or just as a sauce with caramel or something over.
Handy to have when in a hurry.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake pie crust and cool.
Place eggs, sugar, milk, butter, flour and lemon flavoring in saucepan and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: jiffy cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine 3 cups of the flour, cake mix, yeast, salt and warm water.
Mix until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Roll dough into a 9 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough jelly-roll style, starting with the long end.
Slice the roll into 1-inch circles. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 15 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Brush with butter. Yields 18 to 29 rolls.

title: sweet fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will keep for days if you only add enough bananas for each serving.

title: potato corn soup with chiles and cheese
directions: In a 5 quart soup pot over low heat, melt butter.
Add the onion and carrots and cook, covered, stirring once or twice for 20 minutes.
Add the chicken stock, potatoes, cayenne pepper and salt, bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook, stirring occasionally, for about 40 minutes, or until tender.
Cool slightly; then strain the soup, reserving the liquid.
Transfer solids to food processor and process briefly.
Add 1 cup of the reserved liquid to the processor and process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down the sides of the bowl.
Return the puree and the reserved liquid to the soup pot.
Set it over low heat and stir in corn, chiles and milk.
Bring slowly to a simmer.
Taste for correct seasoning and thin further, if desired, with additional milk.
Simmer, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, toss together the grated cheeses.
Ladle soup into bowls, sprinkle each with about 1/3 cup of cheese and serve at once.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add frozen juices and just before serving, add ginger ale.
Yields 25 servings.

title: eggplant salad-bulgaria
