directions: Roast eggplants, peel while still hot and leave on slanted cutting board to drain. Chop after well drained. Place in bowl and mix with wooden spoon, with a little oil at a time mix until it whitens and becomes foamy. Add finely chopped onions, (to taste), pepper, and salt. Place in salad bowl or an a plate and garnish with tomato slices and green pepper slices.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Add lemon juice to 1/2 cup milk.
Place flour and sugar in a bowl; mix well.
Bring margarine, cocoa, water and shortening to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well. Add soda, buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all fruit juices; add ginger ale.
Add orange slices and cherries.
Spoon sherbet into punch.

title: brickle bars
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook and stir margarine or butter and unsweetened chocolate over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat lightly with a wooden spoon just until combined.
Don't overbeat or brownies will rise too high, then fall.
Stir in flour.
Spread batter in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: joan's heavenly salad
directions: Thaw Cool Whip before preparing. Drain all fruit (you can put the juices in a jar and add to Kool-Aid for an extra taste). Do not refrigerate fruit prior to mixing.

title: wally's cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.

title: fire & ice pickles
directions: Drain the pickles. To the pickle juice, add sugar, tabasco and red pepper flakes. Stir and sit for 2 hours. Stir occasionally, pour back into original jars and refrigerate.
Add 1 clove of garlic and 2 whole peppers to each jar.

title: crock-pot chicken-in-a-bag
directions: You will also need 1 cooking bag.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Prepare Uncle Ben's according to directions. While rice is cooking, melt butter in large saucepan. Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in half and half and chicken broth. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Stir in chicken, pimento, rice, parsley and almonds. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sinfully rich potatoes
directions: Put hash browns (frozen) into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle cheese over potatoes. Pour heavy cream and melted butter on top and season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with small amount of paprika, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan caramel rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast with warm water. Stir in 1.4 c sugar, salt, 2 Tbsp margarine, egg and 2 c flour. Beat until smooth. Flour until the dough is easy to handle. If it becomes to sticky, dampen your hands with cold water. Place in a greased bowl. Cover tightly and refrigerate over night, (up to 4 or 5 days).

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix into stuffing.
Mix soup, squash and sour cream.
Layer stuffing mix, then other ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and soups.
Cook broccoli.
Mix in with rice mixture.
Add onion flakes.
Put into baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Make syrup of sugar and water brought to a boil.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans. Put soup and 1/2 can of onions; mix together.
Put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place remaining onions on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place meat in bottom of baking dish.
Put potatoes, peas and mushroom soup, with 1/2 cup water, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook diced potatoes in salted water about 15 minutes.
Blend butter and flour over low heat until bubbly.
Add seasonings.
Add milk, 1/3 cup at a time, stirring constantly.
This will be a thin sauce.
Place potatoes in a shallow oblong glass casserole dish. Pour sauce over potatoes.
Top with lots of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve hot.
Will serve 12.

title: chicken and chips casserole(microwave)
directions: In medium bowl combine chicken, celery, almonds, onion and salt.
In small bowl combine mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into chicken mixture.
Spread chicken mixture evenly in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Cover and cook on High heat for 8 minutes in microwave, stirring after 4 minutes. Stir again and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at High for 1 minute. Top with chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup flour. Sift over top of sweet potatoes; melt and drizzle 1/3 stick margarine over sugar and flour mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 to 2 cups whole pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon chicken n broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, stir cornstarch, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and chicken; saute 4 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook 1 minute. Stir in milk mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Spoon over noodles; toss and serve.

title: one crust pie shell
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into 9-inch pie pan.
Put oil and milk in a small bowl and beat until white and thick.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well using hands to work and shape in pan. If used for soft pie, prick with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425° or until done.

title: boiled raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Boil until raisins are soft and about 1/4 cup liquid remains.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the soda to the cooled raisins.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut crust off bread and toast bread.
Butter toast; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Close up like sandwiches.
Cut into finger slices.
Put into well-buttered casserole.
Sprinkle raisins and brown sugar on top.
Beat eggs and add to milk with 2 tablespoons white sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Place casserole in pan with 1/2-inch water.
Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes.

title: baked finnan haddie
directions: Place serving size pieces of fish in a buttered shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and flour and dot with butter.
Add the milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: Cook pepper and onion in butter until onion is brown, about 5 minutes.
Combine in casserole with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: graham cracker delight cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Set aside. Mix graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and soda. Add to the sugar mixture.
Add milk and mix well. Add vanilla, stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 2 greased 10 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter divinity
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Boil until soft ball in water.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add salt.
Gradually add the syrup to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add powdered sugar until thick enough to roll out on wax paper, which has powdered sugar on paper.
Spread peanut butter on candy and roll. Let stand awhile and slice.

title: 7-up sherbet punch
directions: Let 1 1/2 quarts of sherbet soften in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up gently.
Do not stir.
Float remaining sherbet in scoopfuls on punch.

title: marinated shrimp kabobs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp and peppers, in a large bowl.
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours. Heat broiler.
Arrange shrimp and peppers on skewers.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Turn once; brush with remaining dressing.
Cook until done.

title: oven baked hash browns
directions: In a small bowl, combine paprika, pepper and salt.
Lightly brush each of two baking sheets with 1/2 teaspoon of the oil. Arrange potatoes on baking sheets; brush with 1 teaspoon more oil and sprinkle with half the paprika mixture.
Bake in a 450° oven for about 15 minutes.
Turn.
Brush with remaining 1 teaspoon oil. Sprinkle with remaining paprika mixture.
Continue to bake until potatoes are golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and place in casserole.
Cut cheese in squares.
Sprinkle over broccoli and dot with 1/2 the margarine.
Crumble the crackers and mix with remaining margarine (melted).
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cream sugars, oleo and eggs, then add other ingredients.
Form into balls (small).
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Raisins or chocolate chips can be added.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and chill. Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients for 1/2 minute; stir in blueberries. Fill two 9-inch cake pans halfway.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly before glazing (optional).

title: shephard's pie(main course)
directions: Saute the chopped onion in olive oil in a fry pan.
Add the ground beef and stir till the meat is brown.
At this point I add salt & pepper plus the one egg.
Let this cook for about 10 min. And then add the tomato sauce and the worcestershire sauce.
If there are any left over vegetables such as corn, green beans, peas, carrots etc. add them to this mixture.
Let this cook for about 5 min. and then transfer to a casserole dish.
If you have any left over mashed potatoes, thin them out a bit by adding some milk.
Spread these potatoes on top of the mix in the casserole dish and then top them with the cheddar cheese.
When left over potatoes are not available, I use the instant mix and that works just as well.
I usually pile about 1 inch of potatoes on top. Bake in a 350 degree oven for about 1 hour or when the mixture bubbles on the sides.
Turn the broiler on for a few minutes to melt and brown the potatoes & cheese.
Let stand for 15-20 minutes before serving.

title: rum trifle
directions: Pour rum over nuts and raisins and let stand 1 hour.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package, except use 4 1/2 cups milk. Cool.
Beat 1 cup whipping cream; fold into pudding.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan on low heat; add sugar and eggs.
Cool. Then add all ingredients.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
Mark in squares.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Spread rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with the sugar.
Then sprinkle with the dry strawberry jello.
Sprinkle with the cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Pour 1 cup of water over top and be sure the cake mix is all covered, but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crunchy top bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Drop 1 pint jar of Marshmallow Creme by spoonful over top.
Do not spread.
Bake again for 3 minutes. Spread and bake again 4 minutes.
Cool well, frost.

title: orzo pasta
directions: Prepare pasta or rice according to directions on box.
While pasta or is on simmer, pour olive oil into skillet.
Saute on medium heat:
onions, garlic, peppers, and bouillon cubes. Stirring several times.
When bouillon cubes has dissolved, add pasta or rice and mix.
Add spinach to mixture and saute until bright green.

title: tostada bake
directions: Brown meat with green pepper and onion.
Add olives and seasonings.
Put in shallow casserole.
Spoon sour cream over meat.
Pour beans over evenly; sprinkle with corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over shredded lettuce or hot rice.

title: icebox muffin mix
directions: Soften 100% Bran in hot water and set it aside.
Blend shortening, sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk, bran mixture, flour, soda, salt and All-Bran.
Mix well.
Fill muffin tins as you need.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cover remaining mixture and refrigerate.
Do not stir again even though ingredients seem to settle.
Dip out amount needed.
This mixture keeps well up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, baking in three 9-inch layers (it will take less time than directions say so watch carefully 10 minutes before end of baking time).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in shortening until soft.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook rice; add to mixture.
Add all mixture to a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling through or brown.
Casserole may be prepared and frozen before cooked.

title: chicken and wild rice(microwave)
directions: Place butter or margarine in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, on 100% power for 30 to 45 seconds or until butter is melted.
Skin, bone and cut chicken breast lengthwise in half.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Add chicken strips and peas to melted butter in baking dish; toss to coat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover the dish with vented clear plastic wrap and cook on High about 8 minutes or until peas and chicken are tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Combine rice, pine nuts or almonds and sherry.
Add to chicken mixture; toss to mix.
Cook, covered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pasta kraut
directions: Brown the meat.
Saute onion in the oil. Add soup, sauerkraut, salt and pepper.
Cook the noodles according to directions on package.
Add to meat mixture.
Put in 3-quart casserole that has been greased.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and melted butter. Sprinkle over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes, onions and garlic.
Put 2 trays of ice cubes on top.
Let set 2 hours, or, if desired, let set in refrigerator until crisp.
Drain off water.
In kettle, cook cukes, onions, garlic and remaining ingredients until tender.
Pour into jars while hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, well. Add flour and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Bake in 3 (8-inch) round pans.

title: totally awesome banana pudding
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together.
Add sour cream and 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Mix in pudding mixture with mixer.
Slice bananas and fold in mixture.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer with vanilla wafers.
Top with mixture, then wafers, then mixture.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: glorified hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients except breadcrumbs.
Shape into 12 to 15 balls.
Roll balls in breadcrumbs and then flatten into patties. Crumb patties again; fry until well browned.
Hamburgers may be stored in your freezer before or after cooking.

title: brown rice and mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
(Check after 1 hour.)

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Line shallow baking dish with aluminum foil.
Combine corn flakes, salt, paprika and pepper.
Blend together mustard, vinegar, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, then stir in Pet milk. Dip chicken in milk mixture, then roll in corn flake mixture. Place on foil lined baking dish, skin side up.
Do not crowd. Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.
Do not turn.
Serves 8.

title: meatball-mushroom-broccoli stew
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until golden. Add broth and bring to a boil. Combine beef, water, salt and pepper.

Shape in walnut size meatballs and drop into simmering broth; simmer 10 minutes. Stir in spaghetti. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add broccoli. Cover and cook 10 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Bake the sweet potatoes for 30 minutes, then puree with the soy milk and salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, bake the pastry shells according to package directions.
Take pastry shells from the oven, remove the tops, and fill with the warm sweet potato mixture.
Replace the tops and serve immediately.
Makes 12 sweet potato puffs.

title: caramel butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too thick, add 1/2 teaspoon milk at a time until the right consistency is found.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream together milk, butter and sugar; add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop from spoon on wax paper; pieces should be about the size of small walnuts.
Let set overnight in a cool place.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions. Stir green chiles, cumin, oregano and sage into batter.
Pour into an 8 inch greased, baking pan and bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow to cool and set aside.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Combine into a greased casserole.
Top with Ritz crackers and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until firm at 350°.

title: famous french onion soup
directions: Slice onion 1/8-inch thick.
Melt margarine in large pot. Saute onions for 1 1/2 hours.
Add pepper, paprika, bay leaf and flour; cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add bouillon, water, wine and salt.
Darken with Kitchen Bouquet, if desired. Refrigerate overnight

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
Use about 2 tablespoons oleo for each round.
Make into patties and fry 2 or 3 minutes on each side.
Drain.

title: zesty pot roast
directions: Coat meat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in fat in large, heavy pan.
Combine tomato juice, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours, until tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add strawberries with
juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Put 1/2 mixture into Pyrex dish; refrigerate until firm. When congealed spread sour cream over top, then pour balance of mixture over all. Refrigerate.

title: lo-cal slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, onion, pepper and celery in bowl.
In another bowl, mix oil, vinegar, Equal, salt and pepper together. Stir well.
Combine the oil mixture and cabbage mixture.
Let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Makes a large bowl.
Will keep for 3 days.

title: hot wings
directions: Fry wings.
Mix sauce.
Add wings to sauce.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Or, bake on a rack in roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn once at halfway point.

title: cabbage and pork chops
directions: Brown pork in deep pot.
Chop cabbage and add to pot with pork chops that have been cut into bite size pieces.
Saute cabbage with pork chops, then add 1 (16 ounce) can tomatoes or stewed tomatoes and 1 can tomato sauce.
Season to taste and add a basil leaf.
Eat over rice.

title: great marinade beef kabobs delux
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, vinegar and seasoning.
Whisk.
In shallow container, add meat and marinate 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Parboil potatoes until almost tender.
Alternate meat and vegetables on skewers.
Grill 5 minutes on each side until done as desired.
Baste with marinade.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Mix water and salt.
Add pecans; soak for 2 hours.
Stir often. Take pecans out of water.
Pat dry on paper towel.
Put in pan well-greased with butter.
Cook at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in preheated oven.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
On top of broccoli, place chicken.
In small saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Add chicken stock gradually, stirring until thick.
Add heavy cream, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, mustard, onion, sherry and seasonings.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over meat and broccoli.
Fridge or freeze. Return to room temperature; bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Before serving, dash sherry generously over all.

title: company crab casserole
directions: Cut artichoke hearts in half and place in well-greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with mushrooms and crabmeat.
Melt butter and blend in flour and seasonings.
Add cream gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in sherry.
Pour sauce over crabmeat.
Combine crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until bubbly.
(Good made individually and served with salad and roll for luncheon.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break pasta into bite size pieces; cook and rinse.
Drain well and set aside.
Mix oil, lemon juice and Accent.
Mix into pasta well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add remaining ingredients and season, if necessary.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add minced onion and egg.
Stir to make a stiff batter, adding milk.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil or shortening.
Fry until golden brown, approximately 3 minutes.
Lift out and drain on absorbent paper and serve at once.
Makes approximately 20.

title: dirty rice(a cajun dinner)
directions: Boil giblets in salted water until very tender.
Reserve liquid for cooking rice (adding more water, if necessary).
In deep iron skillet start pork sausage on low heat and as soon as the fat begins to cook out add onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Continue cooking on low heat, stirring occasionally until all vegetables are soft.
Add cooked rice, giblets, green onion tops, parsley, salt and pepper and stir all together thoroughly but lightly.
If possible add some drippings from the fowl or meat which you are serving (better prepared a day ahead).
It freezes well.
Serves 10 to 20.

title: beef noodle stroganoff(in the microwave.)
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes. Stir in water, bouillon, parsley, salt, pepper, mushrooms and noodles. Cover.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes, stirring twice. Stir in sour cream and mustard. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts and chestnuts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts and drain.
Make white sauce.
Melt butter; add flour and add chicken broth and cream.
Add cheese; fold in Brussels sprouts and chestnuts.
Sprinkle with bacon and season.
Reheat in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: company asparagus
directions: Combine asparagus, soup, eggs, almonds and 1/2 cup bread crumbs in buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 cup bread crumbs over mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Simmer margarine, celery and green pepper.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushrooms, Velveeta cheese and stewed tomatoes.
When cheese is melted, add cooked shrimp. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. If you need to, thicken with 3 tablespoons of flour in water. We like ours thin.

title: fun cake
directions: Last we put it in the oven for 15 hours.
Then when it's finisted.
You take it out of the oven.
You cut it and blow on the cake.
The very last thingn is you eat the cake.
But you have to shear with your family and friends.

title: broccoli-rice casserole #1
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Cook broccoli as directed. Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add cheeses and soups, then rice and drained broccoli.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: delicious tender rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour in a large mixer bowl.
Combine milk and butter and heat until very warm 120 to 130 degrees.
With mixer speed on low, gradually beat warm liquid into dry ingredients.
Increase speed, occasionally scraping sides of bowl, and beat 2 or 3 minutes.
(Beating batter early in the combining process helps build the gluten, enabling the rolls to rise better.)

title: honey carrots
directions: Warm honey; add water, ginger and oleo. Stir while cooking over medium heat.
Cook until thick and pour over hot carrots.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix with a fork.
Serve with rye crackers or variety of crackers.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Using 1 box honey graham crackers, line pan with crackers.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Spread pudding, then crackers, then pudding and crackers.
Top with can of chocolate icing or your favorite icing recipe.
Let set at least 24 hours.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 1 or 1 1/2-quart baking dish in oven or microwave.
Meanwhile, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the milk and mix until batter is smooth. Pour this mixture over melted butter in baking dish.
Sprinkle the fruit on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm with whipped cream. (Can be doubled.)

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, pour in the melted margarine.
Add over the top of the margarine the graham cracker crumbs; do not mix. The coconut is then added followed by a layer of chocolate chips, etc., until all 7 ingredients are layered in the pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sour cream drop biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, salt, shortening, milk and sour cream.
Add flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 450° on greased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix butter, sugar and egg; add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour gradually.
Mix well.
Fill desired number of muffin tins about half full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Cover tightly and refrigerate unused portion.

title: potato kugel
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until browned.
Mix eggs with potatoes; sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to potatoes and eggs.
Stir in the onions and the butter in which they were cooked.
Blend well.
Pour into a well-greased one-quart casserole dish and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about one hour.
Edges of kugel should be brown and crisp.
Makes 6 servings.
Top with sour cream.

title: fried apples
directions: In a skillet on medium heat, melt 1 teaspoon bacon grease and 1 teaspoon butter.
Place apples in skillet and sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cover with lid and cook slowly until tender.
Remove lid and cook out the water.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add oil, then rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Grease and flour pans.
Fill about 3/4 full.

title: bea's cake
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve juice) to make 1 cup.
Add water, if needed.
Add pineapple juice to cake mix and eggs and oil if called for.
Beat.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until done at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato and apricot casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over the potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: unbaked fudgies cookies
directions: Blend in a saucepan sugar, cocoa, shortening and milk.
Boil about 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla, then add rest of the ingredients.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter and olive oil.
When limp but not brown, add beef and cook, stirring frequently, until well done.
Add wine; cover tightly and steam for 5 minutes.
Add basil, tomato paste, puree and juice.
Add green pepper, celery, pepper and nutmeg; cook for 10 minutes. Boil lasagna in water for 15 minutes.
Plunge in cold water for ease in handling, then drain.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail and oranges. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fruit cobbler(any kind)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put into baking dish. Stir in fruit.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, then put Miracle Whip on top.
Drain water off and stir.
(Let set overnight.)

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip eggplant in beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet with oil.
Saute onions and mushrooms; drain off fat. Mix brown sugar and tomato sauce and pour over onions and mushrooms.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer eggplant and cheese in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over layers.
Top with grated Mozzarella; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make balls.
Roll in flour. Brown.
Pour over 1 can consomme.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift all dry ingredients thoroughly together.
Blend in oil. Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out in thin rectangle.
Spread sausage and roll up lengthwise.
Chill dough. Slice and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook in oven until thick.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Remove corn from cob.
Put in kettle with other ingredients. Boil 5 minutes.
Cool, put into bags and freeze.

title: pioneer beauty hints(use any that suit your fancy!)
directions: 1) Rinse hands in vinegar and water after they have been in wash water or any soapy water and they will keep soft and pliable.

title: cheese soup
directions: Drain vegetables.
Heat with soup and 2 cans water.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: sally's salmon cakes
directions: Mix salmon, corn meal, flour and egg together and make into patties.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: vanilla glaze
directions: Blend sugar with cream and vanilla.
Beat until of spreading consistency.

title: peanut brittle(microwave version)
directions: Put peanuts, sugar and corn syrup in glass dish. Cook 4 minutes in microwave on High. Stir well. Add pecans.
Cook 4 more minutes, adding vanilla and oleo.
Cook 1 minute, then add baking soda.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until cools. Break into pieces.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald buttermilk in top of double boiler.
Add sugar, salt, soda and melted shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and 1/2 the flour, beating well. Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until satiny.
Shape into small round biscuits and place in a greased pan or roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush each with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry whip - low calorie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 2 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened with the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Remove any remaining ice. Stir in 2 3/4 cups of the whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Spoon into 8 individual dessert dishes.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Makes 8 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples in cider or water until soft.
Strain pulp. To each cup of pulp add 1/2 c. of sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture sheets from spoon.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Store in a cool dry place.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Put marshmallows in the margarine and stir constantly.
Have popcorn already popped.
When marshmallow is melted, mix in popcorn and make into balls.

title: luscious lemon drops
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, whipped topping, egg, lemon juice and lemon peel; stir to mix well but do not overmix.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar, turning to coat well.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil and peel sweet potatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake in shallow baking dish for 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Serve piping hot.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: In a small bowl combine cranberries and powdered sugar. Set aside.
Stir
together
flour,
sugar,
baking powder and salt. Make
a
well in the center.
Combine the egg, milk and oil and add
all
at
once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened. Fold in cranberries.
Grease muffin cups; fill 2/3 full.
Bake
oven
for
to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs; blend in bananas, milk and vanilla.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In small bowl, combine flour, nuts, baking soda and salt; mix well. Add to banana mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 minutes; remove.
Cool completely on wire rack. Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 (16 slice) loaf.

title: mrs. cotter's cheese dreams
directions: Melt in the microwave the cheeses and butter.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until they are stiff.
Stir together all ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture on bread slices; cut in quarters.
Heat in a hot oven at 350° until tops are slightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, rice, mayonnaise and onion together; place in casserole dish.
Brown butter, cornflakes and almonds in skillet.
Sprinkle over casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over fruit.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese and mix together.
Add chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.

title: mama's spice cake
directions: Cream sugar, lard and egg together.
Add 1 cup raisin juice. Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: Melt butter in hot skillet.
Add meat and sear quickly (without burning).
Add onions and fry for 5 minutes.
Add celery, salt, pepper and hot water.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Mix thoroughly and heat to a boiling point.
Add the flavor and thickening ingredients and cook for 20 minutes or until meat is done.
Serve with white rice and the Chinese noodles.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: rhubarb-nut marmalade
directions: Mix rhubarb, juices, orange and lemon in 3-quart casserole; microwave on High 5 minutes, stirring twice or until fruit is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar; microwave, stirring often on High, 20 to 24 minutes or until mixture reaches 220° on instant read thermometer (or sheets from spoon).
Stir in nuts. Cool to room temperature.

title: great chicken casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain.
Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion in oleo until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine noodles, cheese mixture, chicken and salt.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork and bean chowder
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef until brown.
Drain well.
In Dutch oven combine beans, tomatoes, water, onion, bay leaf, seasoned salt, garlic salt, thyme, black pepper and meat mixture. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat, stirring often. Cook 1 hour.
Add potatoes and green pepper.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 8.

title: crisp zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Cut off and discard ends from zucchini.
Slice each zucchini in half lengthwise, then in half again, forming 12 spears.
Combine dry ingredients.
In shallow bowl, combine egg and milk.
Roll zucchini in cornmeal mixture.
Dip into egg mixture, then again in cornmeal mixture to coat thoroughly.
Place in prepared dish. Drizzle with oleo.
Bake 15 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight. Put cherries and nuts on top.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: *You may prefer fresh potatoes, cubed and parboiled (4 to 5).

title: bread pudding
directions: Spread bread with butter or margarine and jam.
Cut into squares and place in a buttered baking dish.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk gradually, stirring constantly and blending well.
Pour mixture over bread.
Set dish in pan of hot water, and bake in a moderate oven for about 1 hour or until pudding is set.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients in large bowl.
Place in meat loaf pan; lay strips of bacon on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours approximately.
Serve with parsley potatoes and applesauce.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together. Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place 4 fillo leaves on top. Sprinkle with butter. Turn fillo at edges toward the rim of the pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease large Pyrex baking dish.
Spread thawed broccoli in bottom of dish.
Mix cheese soup and sour cream.
Spread over broccoli.
Season to taste (salt and pepper).
Crush one tube package of Ritz crackers and scatter on top of casserole.
Pour one stick of melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach pies
directions: In large bowl, wash and chop spinach & onion.
Add salt, pepper, cumin & lemon juice to taste.
Sprinkle with oil and mix. If not ready to use, do not add oil and lemon juice.
It will get soggy.
Heat oven to 400°.
Shape bread dough into balls, 6-8 inch diameter circles.
Fill with spinach mix and fold dough into a triangle.
Spray or put a little oil in a 2 inch deep jelly roll pan.
Heat pan in oven, then place 4-5 spinach pies on pan.
Bake on bottom rack until bottom of pie is golden brown.
Remove tray to top rack to brown.
Remove from tray and brush lightly with leftover juice of spinach mix.
Makes 9 pies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cut sugar and peanut butter until well blended.
Crumble half of mixture into baked pie shell.
To make filling, combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in scalded milk (use double boiler).
Beat egg yolks.
Slowly stir into milk mixture. Cook, stirring until thick.
Stir in oleo and vanilla.
Cool, pour over peanut butter mixture.
Beat egg whites, add sugar, spread peanut butter mixture on top of meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: "nana's" 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine and cook until thick and cool.

title: cream cheese and jelly cookies
directions: Beat margarine and cream cheese until fluffy in a bowl. Combine flour, equal and salt and add to creamed mixture. Refrigerate until dough is firm, about 3 hours.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface to about 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into rounds.
Place rounded 1/2 tsp. fruit into center of each round of dough.
Fold rounds in half and crimp edges with tines of fork. Pierce top of each cookie with the tip of a sharp knife.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
3 doz.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients, oil and corn. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry (375°).
Drain.
Makes 12 to 15 small fritters.

title: jello cools
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
After completely dissolved, add Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl or casserole dish. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Cut up and serve.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix together margarine, eggs, flour, sugar and vanilla (very thick batter).
Spread into ungreased cookie sheet pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling onto batter.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and put in casserole. Cover with topping. Bake at 300° for 30-40 minutes or until brown and crisp.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites and
set aside. Cream margarine and Crisco. Add sugar and egg yolks.
(Do not use light margarine.)
Add alternately with flour, soda and buttermilk.
Add vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Blend in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° until done.
Cool and frost.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine well.
Add flour and Hershey's syrup. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. For icing, use 9 Hershey bars.

title: orange dessert
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups orange juice.
Cool until it starts to jell.
Fold in the stiffly beaten whipping cream.
Break one store bought angel food cake in small bits.
Put one layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of orange, another of cake and top with more orange.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 1/4 cup oleo, sugar, salt, milk, eggs, cinnamon and nutmeg, beating well.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo and top with marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wheaties omelete
directions: Mix Wheaties and eggs together, wetting all of the Wheaties. Add pepper.
Pour the margarine in skillet. Add Wheaties and eggs; cook and scramble over low fire and slow. Don't overcook. Strawberry jam can be added on top after serving.

title: peanut delight
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted butter in bowl; mix well. Spread evenly in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pat evenly and firmly.
Spread ice cream over top.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Spread Cool Whip over peanuts. Cover and freeze.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Bring all ingredients,
except
strawberries, to a boil on top of stove.
Add
strawberries
and
heat
for
2 minutes more. Pour into baked
pie
crust
and refrigerate until set. You may serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: peanut bars
directions: Pour boiling water over the flour and sugar and beat together (it must be boiling water).
Beat the egg whites with the vanilla and baking powder until stiff.
Then mix this with the flour mixture.
Put into a greased and floured pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares and roll in the powdered sugar icing, then roll in peanuts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients, except the diced bacon. Sprinkle the bacon over the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Top the bacon with the meat and vegetable mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Puncture cake with fork.
Pour coconut cream over cake.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with dry coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, measure sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, bring to full boil water, butter and cocoa; remove.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well and add other ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: melon in rum-lime sauce
directions: Cut cantaloupe and honeydew melons in half and remove seeds. With scoop, form balls with all 3 melons working around the seeds in watermelon.
Put melon balls and blueberries in bowl and chill. In small saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add lime rind and let cool at room temperature.
Stir in lime juice and rum.
Pour over melon balls and berries.
Chill, covered, for several hours.

title: red, white and blueberry dessert
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in hot water.
Add cold water and pour into a pan at least 8 x 12-inch.
Refrigerate until firm.
In a small bowl, soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat skim milk but do not boil.
Add milk to gelatin and stir in cheese, vanilla and Equal.
Blend until creamy.
Place on top of firm raspberry layer and refrigerate to set.
Cook 1 pint blueberries in 2 cups water just until soft.
Stir in raspberry jello until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Cool and pour on top of cheese layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 12 to 24 servings (1/12 equals 88 calories, 1/24 equals 44 calories with Equal).

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients, except the cheese.
Blend well until creamy.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in grated cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Spread chicken over top. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Put stuffing crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauce for mini wieners
directions: Melt grape jelly, mix in other ingredients.
Simmer and add mini wieners.

title: fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling, then cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pan.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and toss together.

title: skillet eggplant
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions with milk. Add softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Whip well. Add sliced strawberries and pour in baked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dirty rice casserole
directions: Combine all in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; continue to cook 3 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add confectioners sugar (may need slightly more) to make of spreading consistency.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.

title: meat ball tummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, eggs and steak sauce.
Mix and shape into balls.
Combine Prime Choice, sugar and butter with meat balls in a skillet.
Simmer, covered, until done.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: In a large pot over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onions and garlic about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours. Discard bay leaves.
Ladle into freezer containers.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Freeze.

title: aunt donna's homemade tacos
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper.
Keep on low heat.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder. In second bowl, mix the egg, orange juice, rind and melted butter. Mix first bowl with second bowl. Add 2 tablespoons hot water, chopped pecans and halved cranberries. Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove immediately from pan and wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate. Remove the wax paper and wrap in foil for storage. Can be frozen or kept in the refrigerator.

title: chicken-spinach toss
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
In a bowl combine the pineapple, spinach, chicken, bean sprouts and water chestnuts. In screw-top jar, combine the reserved pineapple juice, oil, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and pepper.
Shake well.
Pour over salad; toss.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 4.

title: crispy cucumber slices
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced vegetables.
Mix. Empty tray of ice cubes in center of vegetables.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Drain vegetables thoroughly.
Pour hot syrup over them.
Heat over low temperature to scalding.
Do not allow mixture to boil.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars.
Seal at once. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, egg, sugar and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix and form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add oatmeal, raisins, nuts, coconut and sour milk.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon and add.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350°; check for doneness.

title: broccoli-onion casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well; set aside.
In same saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, garlic and onion.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Add cream cheese;
stir until melted.
Stir in broccoli.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Does not need an icing.

title: pasta and peppers
directions: Clean and cut bell peppers and frying peppers in bite-size chunks.
Also cut onions in bite-size chunks.
Clean and slice each mushroom in thin slices.
Clean celery stalks; cut each stalk crosswise in 1/8-inch slices.
In a hot pot add 4 tablespoons cooking oil, a bit of butter and crushed garlic.
Saute celery, onions and mushrooms until tender, stirring occasionally.
Lower fire; add peppers and saute for 3 to 4 minutes more.
Remove pot from fire and set aside.
Cook pasta until tender, but firm.
Drain and mix with peppers, etc., in a foil tin.
Garnish each serving with tomato wedges and a bit of chopped parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: bean sprouts with shredded pork
directions: Heat wok.
Add oil; allow oil to heat.
Add pork; saute for 30 seconds.
Add bean sprouts and scallions; cook about 1 minute. Add vinegar and dash of salt.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan turtle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and egg yolk.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Arrange pecan halves in groups of 3 or 5 on greased cookie sheet to resemble head and legs of turtle.
Mold dough into balls; dip bottoms into unbeaten egg white and press lightly into nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost generously.

title: broccoli and mushroom salad
directions: Put vegetables in large bowl.
Cover completely with dressing made of remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil.
Blend well.
Dip chicken pieces.
Place in a shallow baking dish; bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add soda and vanilla to mixture.
Stir in flour, adding enough to make a dough that can be rolled.
Roll dough thin on a heavily floured board.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes, until slightly browned.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix together 1/2 of bag with oleo.
Press into 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Layer onto cookies.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Layer onto cream cheese mixture.
Layer remaining 1/2 of bag of Oreos onto pudding mixture.
Garnish with a few gummy worms if you wish.

title: jelly filled banana muffins(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Mash bananas with potato masher.
Add oil, Egg Beaters and milk and mix with spatula until well blended.
Add sugar and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir until blended. Put into muffin tins with 2 spoons.
Scoop well in center of each muffin.
Put in jelly and re-cover with batter.

title: australian bread(fat-free)
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar until watery.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Put into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in frying pan.
Place orange slice on each chop.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix sugar, sauce and water well; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Layer other vegetables in order given.
Add dressing.
Spread on top of vegetables. Sprinkle cheese on top of all.
Refrigerate until serving time. Put crumbled bacon on top just before serving.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, spices and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on rack. Yields 9 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well, then drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat and cook until brown.

title: berry pie
directions: Mix berries with tapioca. Let set while making crust.
Add sugar to berry mixture and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or more.

title: party jello
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: carolina style barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium sauce pan, combine the vinegar, mustard, sugar, water, chili powder, pepper and tobacco. Simmer for 25 minutes. Add the soy and butter and simmer for 25 minutes longer. Use as you would any barbecue sauce.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with the milk, but with just enough strokes of the spoon to mix it.
Fold in cranberries and orange rind last.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix spices together.
Coat chops.
Melt shortening and cook chops over low heat until brown.
Pour in juice and vinegar. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cook over low heat 40 minutes or until chops are tender when cut with a fork.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Saute onion in small amount of olive oil.
Add rice, tomatoes, seasonings and crumbled bacon.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes, then pour into quart casserole (cover tightly).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and stir with fork several times during cooking process.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in well-greased casserole dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add layer of onions, potatoes and carrots.
Pour soup over top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: strawberry-banana dessert
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, make first layer of bananas.
For second layer, add strawberries.
Put sliced angel food cake over strawberries for third layer.
For fourth layer, make strawberry jello, decreasing cold water by 1/3 cup.
Chill until slightly firm and pour over layers.
Make puddings, decreasing milk by 1/3 cup for fifth layer.
Spread Cool Whip for sixth layer and top with sliced strawberries for seventh layer.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add any combination of the following:
sauteed onions, grated Cheddar cheese, minced bacon, diced green chilies, Trader Joe's tomato splash.
Be creative!

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove mushroom stems and finely chop; set caps aside.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip until thoroughly blended.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set.

title: sausage and egg casserole(shared by my daughter, diane r. gibson)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Pour milk in bowl and add beaten eggs and salt; mix.
Add cubed bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into a greased 8 x 10-inch dish; put in fridge overnight.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving. This is very good to serve for guests coming in for breakfast or brunch.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Mix in M&M's (save about 1/2 cup).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press 3 to 4 M&M's into top of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: banana pie
directions: Grind cookies to powder.
Add melted butter and sugar.
Mix well and cover pie pan with cookies.
With spoon spread mixture until firm.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Fold the mayonnaise and whipped cream into the other ingredients.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; boil until water evaporates. Be careful not to burn peanuts.
Spread on flat pan and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir and bake another 15 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Lightly brown beef in skillet. Add onion and garlic; cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, stirring occasionally for 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken soup with noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in a large saucepan or Dutch oven. Cover. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour or until chicken and vegetables are almost tender. Add noodles; mix well and cook for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl the chicken, apples, pasta, grapes, onion, celery and pineapple chunks.

title: pineapple bavarian cream
directions: Dissolve the contents of package of orange Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water.
Add pineapple juice.
Set in refrigerator and chill until it begins to congeal.
Beat until light and fluffy.
(Be sure to keep cool while beating; preferably set bowl in pan of ice.)
Fold in well-drained crushed pineapple, then fold in 2 cups whipped cream.
Chill until ready to use.
(May be served as a dessert on angel food cake.)

title: no peek chicken
directions: Cut up fryer as usual.
Heat, in saucepan, soups and milk. Add rice to heated soup mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish. Salt chicken pieces and place on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and cook at 300° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: southern green beans
directions: Choose tomatoes that are just beginning to change color. Slice tomatoes and dip in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Let set a few minutes and re-dip if needed.
Fry in butter over medium-low heat until golden. Turn carefully and brown the other side.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir gently but good.
It's thick.
Layer in casserole with lots of crushed lightly buttered Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: miss daisy's sweet and sour chicken
directions: Pour
mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: scrambled eggs with ham
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over boiling water. Combine eggs with cream, salt and pepper.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended.
Pour into top of double boiler.
Cook eggs over boiling water, stirring occasionally 10 minutes.
Add diced ham to eggs and cook, stirring several minutes longer or until eggs are of desired doneness.
Stir in chives.
Add more salt and pepper, if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, blend the cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and pimento.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and pinch around edges to seal.
Brush tops with melted margarine; dip in cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes and chilies.
Add Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar; form in balls.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in hot chocolate with toothpick.
Set on wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
In top of double boiler, mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick (about 10 minutes), stirring constantly.
Slowly add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Stir into remaining mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Spread with meringue made with the egg whites and sugar.
Brown in oven.
Watch.

title: quick goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in a large pan; drain.
Season to taste.
Add pepper, onion and celery.
Saute until peppers are cooked.
Add jar of Ragu and can of tomato soup.
In another pan, cook shell noodles, salted, until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Add to meat sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit soda, salt and baking powder.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat two minutes.
Add eggs and beat two minutes more.
Pour into greased and floured pans (two 8 or 9-inch layer).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Transfer chops into baking dish.
Smother chops with sauerkraut and its juice on top of meat. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic strawberry whip
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Into an electric blender, pour hot water, dry gelatin and 1 cup of the strawberries.
Cover. Blend 30 seconds.
Add crushed ice; blend 20 seconds longer.
Add remaining strawberries.
Blend about 3 seconds.
Pour into chilled serving bowl.
Chill 1 hour or until partially set.
Spoon into serving dishes and garnish with mint, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Layer 1:
Cut the angel food cake into 8 pieces.
Lay side by side into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: devil's delight
directions: Mix well.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pumpkin cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and next 4 ingredients. Chill 4 hours or until firm. Shape into ball to resemble a pumpkin.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Save juice from cooked broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add saved juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Stir in flour until mixture becomes thick. Pour over broccoli.
Add 3 beaten eggs and jar of Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix together. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip with softened cream cheese with mixer.
Add powdered sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Spread on crust.
Top with pie filling.
Also good with blueberry pie filling.
Chill.

title: burnt caramel pie
directions: Blend in saucepan the first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
In a small skillet, melt 1/4 cup sugar; cook and stir until a dark golden brown (use small amount of hot water to liquify).
Add the burnt caramel and milk to saucepan.
Mix until smooth.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Add last 3 ingredients; add slightly beaten egg yolks first and stir for a minute, then last 2 minutes. Whip whites into meringue.
Top with meringue.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Place pork tenderloins in a heavy plastic bag.
Add remaining ingredients.
Seal bag and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.

title: ice tea punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and steep 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: something special casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on box. Add corn, soup, tomatoes and parsley.
Layer half of the macaroni mixture and Spam in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Whip egg whites on medium speed until soft peaks form. Continue whipping on medium speed while gradually adding sugar and baking powder. Continue to whip until very stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.

title: turkey steaks and rice
directions: Mix the flour, paprika, pepper, salt and poultry seasoning in paper sack.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400°.
Coat turkey steaks in paper sack mixture and place in buttered pan. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
While cooking, place water, onions and bouillon into pot.
Bring to boil.
Remove turkey steaks and add onion broth and uncooked rice to butter in bottom of pan. Place turkey steaks (turned over from early baking) on rice.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: rocks
directions: Mix butter and sugar together until soft. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, soda and cinnamon together and add to egg mixture.
Add chopped dates and pecans to batter with the water. This will be very stiff to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown diced onion in liquid Butter Buds.
Add cooked ground turkey.
Stir refried beans into turkey mixture.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle green chilies over top of turkey-bean mixture.
Spread 1/2 of cheese over this.
Pour taco sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and spoon sour cream to make a cross on top of casserole.
Serve with Smart Temptations low-fat tortilla chips or homemade low-fat chips.
Yields 16 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: all-in-one hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together ground beef and chopped onion. Mix together salt, pepper, chili powder and flour in a small bowl. Place the instant rice in a buttered 3-quart casserole and 1/3 of the flour mix. Put a layer of ground beef and onion next.

Pat about 1/3 of the flour mixture on top of the beef. Dot with margarine. Put the can of tomatoes and another 1/3 of the flour mixture on next. Dot with margarine. The last layer should be the can of corn, including liquid. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 generously.

title: oil pastry
directions: Pour salad oil in large measuring cup; add cold milk.
Do not stir milk and oil together.
Mix flour and salt; add oil and milk mixture, stir together.
For best results, moisten countertop slightly and roll out between 2 sheets waxed paper.
Makes 2 pie shells or 1 double crust.

title: wild game swiss steak
directions: Roll round steak in flour.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil or 3 tablespoons.
Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Add sliced onion.
Pour tomatoes over all and simmer for 1 hour.
May take longer if meat is on the tough side.
Can use beef also.

title: wells' many bean soup
directions: Mix together thoroughly all beans, except pink, red and black beans.
Divide into eight 1 pound packages.
Save.

title: fast fixing chocolate cake
directions: Spread oil evenly over bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add other ingredients, stir until well mixed.
(Don't add pudding if it is already in cake mix.)
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: grilled swordfish with baked tomatoes and zucchini mardi gras
directions: Marinate swordfish overnight, preferably brushing with 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon blackening spice - if less spicy marinade preferred, use 1/2 teaspoon spice.

title: raisin oatmeal bars
directions: Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Mix next 5 ingredients together.
Divide 2/3 and 1/3.
Pat 2/3 into 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour filling on top.
Sprinkle 1/3 of oatmeal mixture on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-pecan honeyed chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in margarine on both sides. Add orange juice, honey, onion and pepper.
Salt to taste.
Cover loosely and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and arrange on bed of rice.
Keep warm.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients, except nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Spoon into buttered pan; cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: hidden valley layered mexican dip
directions: Mix dip mix with sour cream. Spread refried beans in a serving dish. Spread dip mix on top of beans and top with Cheddar cheese and olives. Garnish with tomatoes and green onions.

title: reese's bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Add powdered sugar and wheat germ.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and spread on top.

title: spaghetti ajo e ojo
directions: Both the spaghetti and the sauce can be made at the same time. Make the spaghetti according to the package directions; cook al dente.
In a small saucepan, put in the olive oil, garlic and salt over low heat; stir often.
When the garlic is a golden brown, the sauce is ready.
Pour over spaghetti and mix thoroughly.
Pepper and parsley the top and serve.
Serves 4.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Mix seafood, cheese, onions, pimiento and cream cheese; place in bottom of pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over crab, etc., which is in bottom of pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Drain oranges and reserve 1/2 cup juice. Add soy sauce to orange juice. Add onion and cornstarch to mixture. Stir up well. Brown chicken pieces in butter and garlic salt.
Add sauce and simmer with lid for 30 minutes. Add a little water if it thickens too much.
About 5 minutes before serving, add oranges and pepper. Replace lid and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter in bowl in microwave.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir well.
Add evaporated milk; mix well.
Add confectioners sugar slowly and mix well. Microwave for 2 minutes; turn bowl and mix.
Microwave 1 minute; remove and stir well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cider.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth; add to cider.
Slowly bring to boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot with orange slice and cinnamon stick.
Serves 12.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil and seasonings; pour over crackers in long flat pan. Mix well with wooden spoon.
Let stand 1 hour and place in a plastic container.
Do not refrigerate.

title: rouladen
directions: Pound top round (halves if large).
Roll pickle in meat and surround with bacon.
Fasten with toothpick.
Salt and pepper and brown in butter.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion, garlic, carrots, tomatoes, allspice, herbs, wine, 1 cup water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove meat and blend in remaining water and flour.
Cook and stir until sauce boils for 1 minute.
Reduce heat and return meat.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add orange juice.
Blend well and chill.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Beat well with mixer.
Pour into prepared crust.
Place in refrigerator while making the meringue.
To make meringue, beat the separated egg whites until peaks form.
When meringue peaks, gradually add sugar until well mixed, then add the cream of tartar or lemon juice. Pile onto top of pie.
Place in 400° oven for 4 to 5 minutes or until top of meringue browns lightly.

title: carrot dogs
directions: Please don't knock these until you have tried them.

title: hot cider
directions: Pour apple cider in percolator.
Put about 1/3 cup cinnamon red hots in percolator basket.
Perk and serve hot.

title: chip beef casserole
directions: Mix all together; add 2 chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Stir gently; store covered in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and cook at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ellen's rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until onions are translucent.
Add peas and corn; combine with onions, etc.
Add water and bouillon; bring to boil.
Add rice and grated Parmesan. Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: sally lunn (bread)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Add well-dissolved yeast and milk alternately with flour, stirring until smooth.
Last, fold in beaten egg whites.
Let rise 4 hours in same bowl.
Beat down and put into well-greased chimney pan (this dough does not pour; must be smoothed into pan with wooden spoon) and let rise 1 hour.
Bake in slow (350°) oven for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.
Is delicious hot; also sliced cold and toasted for breakfast.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg and sugar with mixer.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour into freezer container.
Freeze and enjoy!

title: ranger joe cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla to the above mixture; mix until smooth.
Add the flour, 2 teaspoons vanilla, salt, rolled oats, corn flakes and coconut.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Don't leave to cool on pans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and sugar 2 loaf pans.

title: red bean chili dip
directions: Heat the oil in small pan.
Add the onion and garlic.
Fry gently for 4 minutes.
Add the spices and fry for 1 minute.
Stir in tomato paste and vinegar.
Leave to cool.
Place the beans, cheese and onion mixture in a blender or food processor.
Work until the consistency of thick mayonnaise.
Add a little water if necessary.
Check the seasoning.
Chill until required.
Serve with raw vegetables or tortilla chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: brown soup stock
directions: *The peel is what gives the stock much of its color.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake as many potatoes as you need.
Cut a strip off the top so you can scoop out the inside.
Mash as mashed potatoes, only use margarine and cream cheese, salt, pepper and seasoned salt. Re-stuff
the
potatoes.
Top with grated jalapeno Jack cheese and
Cheddar, mixed.
Bake before ready to serve about 10
to
12 minutes at 350°.
(If cold out of the refrigerator, it
may
need longer
baking time.) Can be made ahead of time nicely.

title: zucchini casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 in bottom of casserole (9 x 12-inch).
Mix sour cream, soup, onion and zucchini.
Spoon over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat butter and sugar together for 10 minutes with an electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and lemon extract and mix to blend. Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into heavily greased Bundt pan and bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in the pan.
Makes 16 servings.

title: dessert coffee mix
directions: Place ingredients in blender on high.
For each serving, place 2 teaspoons in cup.
Fill with boiling water.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix everything in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until rice is tender.

title: baby hot browns
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add half and half.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add flour.
Whisk and cook until mixture is frothy and raw flour taste is gone.
While stirring, add the bouillon mixture.
Stir constantly with a whisk until the sauce thickens and begins to bubble.
Add Swiss cheese and stir until smooth.
(If sauce needs to be thinned, heat and add a little water.)
Assemble Hot Browns by placing turkey and onion on each bread slice.
Top with sauce and crumbled bacon.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: zucchini bake(microwave)
directions: In a covered, 2-quart casserole, cook zucchini with butter for 5 minutes on full power.
Mix eggs and cheese together and add to zucchini.
Cook on Defrost or Simmer for 10 minutes, covered. Sprinkle onion rings on top and cook 2 minutes more on Defrost or Simmer, uncovered.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer for 1 1/2 hours to chill.
Add one small Cool Whip for topping and serve.

title: pork-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place chops in shallow baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. pour into a greased loaf pan. Combine 1 Tbsp. brown sugar, 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and 1 Tbsp. melted butter. Mix well and spread over top of batter. Bake 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop other vegetables fine.
Mix spices, sugar, flour, salt and vinegar.
Add chopped vegetables and corn. Cook 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: meat whirl
directions: Mix meat,
crumbs,
egg,
mustard, salt, pepper, horseradish and part of tomato sauce.
On waxed paper, pat meat in 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Spread with
cheese
and
roll as jellyroll. Press ends to seal. Transfer to baking dish
seam
side down. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then pour on
remaining tomato sauce and sprinkle with dill seed.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: great-grandmother sieker's cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, shortening, butter and eggs until well blended.
In small bowl, mix sour cream and baking soda.
Add to other mixture; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Keep in refrigerator until ready to roll out; shape as desired. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peach or pineapple dessert
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until thick.
Drain the fruit and add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over a layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with another layer of wafers.

title: apple betty
directions: Layer apples in a greased, 1-quart baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add margarine and stir with a fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle the flour mixture over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: bucket steak
directions: Put soup, water and sauce in a baking dish. Flour steak and brown on both sides in skillet. When brown, place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
