directions: Cook hamburger and sausage until browned; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together guacamole dip and cream cheese.
Spread beans in large pie plate.
Cover with guacamole and cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle onions, olives and grated cheese over top.
Garnish with tomato slices.
Serve as a dip with chips.
Makes lots.

title: roquefort dressing supreme
directions: Mix the buttermilk, lemon juice, seasonings and grated onion in a large bowl and stir until smooth.
Blend in the mayonnaise and Roquefort cheese.
Mix thoroughly, leaving a few lumps.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Yield: 1 1/2 pints.

title: ham hocks and northern beans
directions: Wash beans and remove any dark sediment.
Put the beans in a large bowl (3-quart size).
Cover almost to the brim with water and let soak for 3 to 4 hours.
Put ham hocks in a large, 5-quart pot and cook until they are tender to the bone.

title: trifle
directions: Cook pudding as directed. Let cool.
Break up cake into bite size pieces. Layer in a trifle bowl or large glass bowl, beginning with cake, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat until filled.
Finish with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh whole strawberries.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix together 1 large can of pineapple with juice and the instant pudding.
Let set 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add Cool Whip.
Very good on angel food cake.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mix sugar, water and cornstarch; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O and strawberries, which have been stemmed, washed and drained.
Pour into pie crust.
When cool, cover with Cool Whip.

title: chili pepper quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell for 3 minutes at 400°.
Prick with fork. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Layer Cheddar cheese, 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese, chilies and remaining Monterey Jack cheese in shell.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in half and half.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix cherries with 2/3 cup sugar.
Melt butter in iron skillet. Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over the melted butter in skillet.
Pour cherries on top. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until nicely browned. (If recipe is doubled, use the juice from only 1 can of cherries.) Easy and delicious!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a large pot. Bring to a boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well, until mixture has no shine.
Drop on waxed paper with a spoon.
Let set until cookies are firm and then refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put the package of cake mix into a mixing bowl.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Divide the batter among three 8-inch layer cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the batter springs back when lightly touched in the center with the fingers.
Cool.
Ice.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and shape into balls. Brown meat balls in skillet.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls in a skillet.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Combine in blender; refrigerate.
Will keep for 1 week or longer in refrigerator.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add nuts and apples.
Mix all together, not with electric beater.
Place in a lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: aunt mary's cheesecake
directions: Cream sugar and cheese using electric beater.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in sour cream. Butter a spring-form pan.
Dust buttered pan with 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Don't open door.
Let stand overnight.
Refrigerate the next day and cut with a hot knife after removing sides of pan.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add beef and all other ingredients to crock-pot.
Heat for 1 hour on high.
If you prefer, you may heat in regular pan on low heat until all ingredients are melted and mixed together.
Keeps well for several hours on low in a crock-pot.
Use for dipping Tostitos, other chips, etc.

title: lettuce delight
directions: Mix together; spread 1/2 pint mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, top with 4 boiled and sliced eggs and bacon bits.

title: mother-in-law's rolls
directions: Scald milk; let cool to warm.
Stir in sugar, salt and lard (or shortening).
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to milk mixture.
Make dough by stirring in flour.
Let rise to double in size.
Punch the dough down and knead it, adding more flour if necessary to keep it from being sticky.
Roll out on a floured surface and cut rolls with a biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet or pan and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until browned.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine pineapple with marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator ovenright.
Mix remaining juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take sauce and add to Cool Whip mix and then add remaining ingredients.
Put in bowl.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: pickles from overgrown cucumbers
directions: Remove seeds from cucumbers.
Soak in crockery or enamel container for 24 hours with lime, dissolved in water.
Rinse well. Cover with ice water and soak 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter until light (3 to 4 minutes).
Add sugar 1/4 cup at a time.
Beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Mix together flour and soda.
Add alternately with sour cream, beating well.
Add vanilla and almond flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with hands until smooth.
Roll into balls.
Bon appetit!!

title: beef stew
directions: Boil bone 3 or 4 hours. Add water as needed. In last hour, add veggies, onion and stew meat sprinkled with Adolph's meat tenderizer. Last 30 minutes, add canned tomatoes or you can use V-8 vegetable juice. Heat through.

title: johnny
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet.
Season with garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper and pinch of sugar.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and corn. When cheese is melted, add cooked and drained macaroni.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half of this mixture into a very hot greased pan or iron skillet. Sprinkle cheese over mixture, then pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lunch-in-a-dish for one or two
directions: Place 2 slices of bread in casserole dish.
Put slices of cheese on bread.
Top with another slice of bread to form a sandwich.
Beat egg and milk together and pour over sandwich. Bake at 350° until custard is absorbed and bread is brown and puffy.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls.
Mix other ingredients together and spread on both sides of rolls.
Sprinkle with ham and replace tops.
Heat and serve.

title: turkey divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend mayonnaise and flour in saucepan over low heat.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring, until thickened.
Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package; spoon dinner into 10 x 6-inch baking dish, arrange broccoli spears and turkey slices over the macaroni.
Top with mayonnaise, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes covered.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or with Cool Whip.

title: momma's pudding
directions: For chocolate pudding use 1/4 c. cocoa.
May omit cocoa and use bananas instead.
Also good with pineapple.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: In saucepan,
mix
all
ingredients except crackers and bread. Bring to a
boil,
add crackers and bread.
In a Pyrex dish, greased or
sprayed
with
Pam, pour all ingredients and bake in a 400° oven
for
30 minutes;
reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until set.

title: cheddar cheese pecan ball
directions: Bring cheese and cream cheese to room temperature.
In mixing bowl, beat cheeses sour cream, mustard and onion powder with electric mixer on medium speed until well combined.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Shape cheese mixture into ball.
Coat ball with chopped pecans.
Transfer to cheese server and serve with favorite cracker.
Store in refrigerator. Keeps up to 1 week.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Can be poured in bowl or mold.
Chill.

title: old fashion apple crisps
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle apples with 1/2 of mixture.
Combine sugar, flour, egg, salt and baking powder.
Spread over apple slices. This will act like pie crust dough.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and brown sugar over contents.
Pour melted butter over top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Blend the eggs, milk and butter in a small bowl.
In a larger bowl, mix the sugar, flour and berries.
Pour the wet mixture into the dry and carefully fold together until all is moist.
Don't beat or smooth it.
Grease muffin tins (or paper liners) and fill 2/3 full.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.
Makes 12 or 18 small muffins.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Combine in electric blender.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and scramble in frying pan.

title: nutted wild rice
directions: Heat the raisins and sherry in a small saucepan to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Place the wild rice, 2 cups of the boiling stock and 2 tablespoons of the butter in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Cook covered for 1 hour.
Place the brown rice, remaining 2 2/3 cups boiling stock and 2 tablespoons of the butter in a medium size saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and cook until all the water is absorbed, about 50 minutes.
Saute the almonds in the remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a small skillet over low heat until lightly toasted.
Combine the wild rice, brown rice, raisins with sherry, almonds and parsley in a large mixing bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove to a serving bowl and serve immediately.

title: chicken veronique
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add chicken and cook until brown, about 4 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to platter; keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium. In the same skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion; cook until tender, about 2 minutes. Add wine, chicken broth, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Increase heat to medium-high and bring mixture to a boil while scraping up browned bits. Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Add cornstarch mixture to skillet.
Cook 1 minute until thickened. Stir in grapes. Spoon over chicken and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and celery in butter.
Add flour and Ro-Tel tomatoes, mixing well.
Add crawfish tails; cook for 15 minutes.
Add cream and cheese, then cook 30 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add crawfish mixture to cooked noodles.
Pour in casserole dish; cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chili
directions: Start beans, onion and pepper to simmering.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup and ground beef to beans.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, peanut butter and butter in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: sand tart treasures
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Sift together in another large bowl the remaining ingredients.
Add sifted mixture to creamed mixture in parts. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with favorite cookie cutters (or press dough in molds).
Decorate with colored sugar, sprinkles, etc., before baking, or decorate with icing when cool.
Bake at 350° on greased sheets until golden. Cool on waxed paper.
Store in covered containers.
Cookies are very easily broken.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Saute the liver in an iron skillet until well done.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add salt and pepper and chopped egg, then margarine.
Let cool.
Put all through a grinder or chop in a glass chopper.
Mix well and put in a nice bowl.
Sprinkle with paprika and a little of the chopped egg.
Good with any kind of cracker.

title: cream pie
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with butter.
Add cream and milk to sugar mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix and shape into meat balls.
Brown in oil.
Pour off excess oil and add the following:

title: citrus spritzer
directions: Place citrus strips in a glass pitcher; crush slightly by gently pressing against pitcher with back of a spoon.
Add juices; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water.
Serve over ice.
If desired, garnish with orange and grapefruit curls.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: After meat is browned, in same skillet add water chestnuts. Add 1/2 small bottle soy sauce or less to cover meat and chestnuts.
Add vegetables.
Cover; let steam.
When tender to desire, add 1 jar sweet and sour sauce and stir.
Top with 1 package cashews.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: rice krispies cheese bits
directions: Mix all ingredients at room temperature.
Make small balls (about a teaspoon) and press flat on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm or cool.
Makes about 3 dozen Cheese Bits.

title: merry chris "mousse"
directions: In microwave saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; blend until combined.
Let set for 2 minutes.
Place in microwave and heat for 40 seconds.
Set aside until cool, approximately 5 minutes.

title: hot dogs and bacon
directions: Cut hot dogs in quarters and cut bacon in half.
Wrap each hot dog in bacon and bake on a cookie sheet for 1/2 hour at 350. Place hot dogs in a crock-pot.
Heat on low 3-4 hours with ketchup and sugar sauce.

title: never-the-same bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse the dried peas and beans.
Put in a large crock-pot or slow cooker and turn setting up fairly high (I use the next-highest setting on my slow cooker and leave it for several hours).
Add bouillon, tomatoes, onion and pepper (if desired).
Walk away from it and resist lifting cover until one hour before serving time.
At that time, add the rice and a little Cajun seasoning.
Check to be sure the rice is cooked before serving.
Enjoy!!

title: chow chow
directions: Coarsely grind onions, tomatoes, green and red peppers, and (hot) green and red peppers.
Add cabbage. Sprinkle with pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together in a jar and shake well.
Have your cabbage grated and mix together.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill well before serving.

title: honey glazed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seed and fiber.
Place in shallow baking pan, cut side down.
Add 1/2-inch of water.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove squash from pan; discard water.

Trim a small slice from bottom of squash so squash will stay level while baking. Combine all remaining ingredients and spoon into squash centers. Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: chili pie casserole
directions: Spread 2 cups corn chips in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and 1/2 cup cheese on top of corn chips.
Pour chili over this.
Top with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Toppings to pass around include diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce and sour cream.

title: katherine's salad
directions: Mix vinegar and oil.
Add olives, artichokes and mushrooms. Stir gently and chill.
When ready to serve, fill a large salad bowl with crisp lettuce.
Pour marinated mix over salad greens. Slice onion, tomato and cucumber on top.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve with the following dressing.

title: apples and carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 300° about 1 hour or 350° about 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips and add peanut butter.
Pour over Chex and stir quickly.
Dump into paper bag with powdered sugar and shake real well.

title: layered enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off any fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce; simmer.
Using a 9-inch square casserole, add enough of the meat sauce to cover the bottom, then alternate layers, starting with a tortilla, meat sauce and cheese.
Add water around edges.
Cover with foil and bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Layer the chicken on top of the broccoli.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients. Layer tortillas torn into pieces, meat mixture and cheese until gone. End with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Chop onion on bottom of casserole dish.
Slice potatoes on top of onion.
Layer onion and potatoes then place pork chops in another layer.
Cover casserole and bake for 3/4 hour at 400°. Remove cover and brown chops for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: juanda's mexican corn bread
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients and in shortening. Add beer and mix well. Drop in a greased muffin pan. Bake at 375° until golden brown. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: spinach puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Drop by teaspoon size portions onto a baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: egg salad filling for 50
directions: Peel eggs; chop coarsely (or blend smooth).
Combine rest of ingredients.
Adjust seasoning.
Add eggs and mix lightly. Refrigerate immediately until well chilled.
Good to serve on croissants with chips and dill pickle spears.

title: fried potato bread
directions: Beat mashed potatoes, shortening, milk and salt until no lumps remain.
Cover and refrigerate until completely chilled, at least 4 hours.
Turn potato mixture onto floured surface.
Knead in flour (dough will be soft); divide into 20 equal parts.
Shape each part into a ball.
For best results, work with 4 or 5 balls at a time.
Cover and refrigerate remaining balls until needed.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire, curry powder, oregano, dry mustard, garlic clove, Tabasco and dry vermouth. Bring combined ingredients just to boiling. Pour over chicken. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: great party punch
directions: Mix all together and chill before party.
Put in serving bowl and serve.

title: fresh strawberries with cream dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, confectioners sugar and orange flavoring until smooth.
Chill 1 hour.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixing bowl. Cut banana into small cubes.
Pour oil and milk into bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Add banana.
Mix.
Pour desired amount of mixture onto hot grill to form pancakes.
Turn over when bubble starts to form.
Makes 8 to 10 large pancakes.
Add more milk if thinner pancake is desired.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk, blending well. Add enough milk or water to make mixture soupy. Pour into a greased 9x13 inch pan. Bake uncover at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

title: luncheon tuna salad(serves 9)
directions: Dissolve gelatine in boiling water.
Add vinegar and salt. Mix well and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly oiled 9-inch square pan; chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit well; top with coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: Thinly slice the bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice and arrange on bottom of baked pie shell.
Stir strawberry ice cream to soften slightly; spread atop bananas.
Freeze until firm. Spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Freeze again until firm.
Pie needs to stand at room temperature for only a few minutes before serving.
Serve with canned chocolate sauce or prepare Quick Fudge Sauce.

title: spuggetties
directions: Put cheese in the macaroni.
Cook it in the oven for 50 hours. Eat!

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: dilled sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with carrot, cucumber and zucchini slices. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: ham casserole
directions: Layer as listed in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are tender.

title: pumpkin pie(makes two 10-inch pies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in a large bowl with wire whisk.
Beat eggs with a fork only until all yellow.
Add beaten eggs and milk to above mixture.
Add pumpkin last, mixing thoroughly with whisk.
Pour into bottom pie crust (uncooked).

title: katie's plain bread
directions: Mix all
but flour.
Add 5 cups flour and mix with hook or knead
in
more
flour
until you have soft, elastic dough. Let rise
until
big, 30 minutes.
Knock down, shape into loaf pans or into
French
bread shapes.
Brush French bread types with beaten egg
before last rising.
Bake until almost done, take out
and cool.
Reheat for 10 minutes in 400° for crusty French loaves.

title: quick microwave pudding
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch.
With a hand mixer or whip, beat in milk and egg yolks until smooth. Microwave on Medium for 5 minutes. Beat well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir. If not thick, continue for 1 to 2 minutes. Blend in butter and vanilla.
Cool, covered with plastic wrap directly on pudding to avoid skin on top.
Good warm or cold. (Can also double recipe.
Just microwave about 12 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.)

title: mom's special green beans
directions: Cook onion in butter until clear.
Add golden mushroom soup and curry powder; mix well.
Let mixture get warm, then add green beans.
Put in a casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted into beans.

title: tomato meat sauce
directions: Heat oil, add onion and garlic and cook until lightly brown. Add meat and brown on both sides. Add tomatoes and paste, salt, pepper, basil and bay leaf.
Cover saucepan and simmer over very low heat for about 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If sauce becomes too thick, add 1/2 cup water.

title: easy country steak
directions: Place steak in lightly greased casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with French fried onions.
Heat soup, water and Kitchen Bouquet until well blended.
Pour over steak. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla. Gradually add flour to creamed mixture; mix thoroughly. Chill for ease in handling. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar and place on baking sheet. With bottom of glass, flatten to 1/4-inch thickness. Place pecan half into center of each cookie. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until lightly brown. Cool slightly. Remove to wire rack to cool. Makes 6 dozen.

title: rich muffins
directions: Sift flour with sugar and baking powder.
Combine eggs, shortening, and milk.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Add liquids all at once and mix only until all dry are moist. Fill well greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
If desired, add 1/2 cup fruit of choice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, flour and pepper together, first softening margarine in microwave.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Form small balls and place on cookie sheet.
(Grease cookie sheet, if necessary.)
Press slightly with fork to flatten cookie. Bake at 315° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt sadie's potato salad
directions: Begin with layer of cabbage in bowl.
Add layer of potatoes, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with celery seed.
Add onion rings and pepper rings.
Add sliced eggs and then spread mayonnaise over all.
(This is the magical ingredient.)
Start all over, adding as many layers as needed for your bowl, ending with eggs and mayonnaise.
Will serve about 10 or more.
This mixture must be refrigerated at least 24 hours before serving.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix ingredients to get a good consistency for modeling.
Let kids create yummy sculptures, then gobble up!
Great for kindergarten class, Sunday school class and grand kids.
Protect table by covering with freezer paper, wax side up and let kids at it.
Quick clean up, to!

title: pork chops on rice pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Season chops with salt and pepper and brown in shortening. Remove chops and brown uncooked rice in drippings. Add remaining ingredients to rice. Place chops over rice. Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
Set until firm.
Unmold on lettuce and serve with sour cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix whole kernel corn, yellow cornmeal, cream-style corn, milk, eggs, cooking oil, soda and salt.
Brown the ground beef. Salt and pepper to taste. Drain the grease off; set aside.

title: german apple cake
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Add oil and mix to this the vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix by hand.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together noodles, hamburger, soups and pizza sauce.
Mix well.
Add oregano.
Layer pepperoni in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour noodle mixture over pepperoni.
Add another layer of pepperoni, then another layer of noodles.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until cheese is brown.

title: shrimp spread open face sandwiches
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender.
Spread on bread and cut into shapes and sizes as desired.
This can be made several days ahead of time.
Keep refrigerated until used.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat condensed milk for 1 minute.
Add whipped topping gradually.
Drain all fruits completely.
Pour lemon juice over fruit and stir to coat.
Fold fruits into whipped topping mixture. Pour into crusts and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 tsp. salt. Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat till fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating till well combined. Cover and chill at least 3 hours. Working with half of the dough at a time, on lightly floured surface roll to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes or until done. Makes 36 to 48.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chinese shrimp
directions: In frypan, cook water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and mushrooms in butter 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in bouillon and cornstarch, mixing well.
Stir in water, shrimp, soy sauce, ginger and onions. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes until shrimp are firm and pink.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa together in a saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minutes.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter to mixture and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: rondele cheese ball (or spread)
directions: Soften cheese and margarine.
Stir in other ingredients. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: california crabs mia
directions: *Hot oil may be purchased in gourmet sections in some major food stores.

title: english muffin breakfast
directions: Fry egg and bacon at same time.
Allow yolk to harden a little.
Toast English muffin while egg and bacon are frying. When done toasting, place a piece of cheese on each piece.
This will allow cheese to melt.
Egg and bacon should be done.
Place on English muffin.
Serves one person.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix melted oleo, flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over hot crust and bake 25 more minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool before cutting.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Lightly grease and flour large cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites and salt at high speed until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually beating at high speed until sugar is completely dissolved; beat in vanilla.
Fold in coconut and flour.
Drop onto prepared cookie sheet 1 tablespoon at a time, about 1 inch apart.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until slightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet with metal spatula onto wire rack to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Use in 3 days.

title: tea cakes
directions: Prepare flour as if to make homemade biscuits.
Add ingredients and use hand to mix ingredients into flour.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake until light brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix soup and sour cream until well blended; pour over beans.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 375° until hot, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8 generously.

title: rich moist coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Puncture top of cake with long fork.
Mix 1/2 coconut with milk.
Spoon on cake, working into holes made by fork.
Whip cream; add vanilla and sugar plus 1/2 cup coconut.
Spread on cake.
Put remaining coconut on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot hominy bake
directions: Mix hominy, browned and scrambled sausage, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cubed cheese.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake until cheese is slightly browned.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Take 1 teaspoon dough.
Put a Rolo candy in center of dough and cover with knife.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: crisp noodle chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in casserole dish.
In a bowl combine soup, sour cream, soup mix and pepper; blend thoroughly. Spread over chicken; sprinkle with noodles.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: black walnut refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening until blended.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add nuts.
Stir in flour until well mixed.

title: smooth mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cheese in small pieces and then butter.
Beat well.
Add sour cream.
Beat eggs into milk and onions.
Add to potatoes and beat until fluffy.
Pour into greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (uncovered) until light brown.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine oats, peanut butter and cocoa; set aside.
Make syrup of sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour syrup over oats mixture and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let set.

title: mama's lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in gradually the hot water.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Beat a little of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Beat into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Pour into pie shell and let cool. Top with meringue and brown at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl until frothy; set aside.
Combine sugar and water in 2-quart pan.
Place on moderate heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Bring to full boil and cook for 3 minutes. Gradually stir hot syrup into eggs.
Blend butter and vanilla into mixture.
Arrange pecans in desired pattern.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Mix lard, flour and salt until it resembles coarse crumbs. Mix egg, brown sugar, vinegar and water.
Stir in flour mixture. Roll out dough and put into pie plate.

title: mexican hash
directions: Cook meat and onion until done; drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours or more.
Serve over Doritos chips, chopped lettuce or chopped tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together rice, corn, garlic, green onion, milk, chili powder, red pepper seasoning, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese. Pour into casserole.
Arrange tomato slices on top, overlapping slightly.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
(Works best if hard cheese is put through grinder.)
Form into balls and roll until covered with crushed pecans if desired.
Makes 6 balls.

title: filet mignon kabobs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add beef cubes.
Marinate 1 hour at room temperature.
Thread beef, pepper, onions and pineapple, alternately on wood or metal skewers. Broil 15 minutes to desired doneness, brushing with marinade and turning.

title: turkey soup
directions: Cook turkey necks in 2 qts. water until tender.
Remove meat from bones and return to broth.

Cook celery, carrots, and onion in a small amount of water until done and add to turkey mixture. Brown flour, black pepper, salt, garlic powder, and Greek seasoning in 3 Tbsp. oil and add to turkey mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons per cup.
Fill with hot water.

title: wassail
directions: In a large saucepan, add all ingredients and enough water to dilute frozen juices plus 2 cups.
Heat to desired temperature. Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks and serve.

title: velvet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in marshmallows.
Add cold water.
Drain pineapple and set aside juice.
Stir in pineapple and bananas.
Pour in long Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: 5 minute devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise 1/3 at a time.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can be baked in 2 (9-inch) layers or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Ice as desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch dish; set aside.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place chops in a glass casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate overnight, turning several times.
Grill over medium coals and baste occasionally with the marinade.

title: stove top yams
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add potatoes.
Pour sugar over potatoes and cook for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and water and cook until yams are done.

title: rosa maria salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then run through cold water.
Drain fruit and cook fruit juice with sugar, flour, salt and beaten eggs until thick.
Mix macaroni with thickened mix.
Let set overnight in refrigerator so it is chilled.
Loosen chilled macaroni with fingers, easy.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Decorate.

title: holiday frozen salad
directions: Add juice to flour to make a paste in double boiler. Add butter, sugar and salt. Cook 10 minutes. Add egg slightly beaten and cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Let cool and add fruit, nuts and marshmallows. Fold in whipped cream. Place in freezer.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: Cut cauliflower into florets (about 3 c.). Cook in boiling salted water to cover 10 to 12 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Place in shallow baking dish.

title: won tons
directions: Chop garlic into little pieces.
Mix garlic, ground pork, salt and pepper in bowl.
Take one wrapper, place 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in center of wrapper and fold to form triangle.
Seal wrapper with water to edge.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions. Spread rice in bottom of a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken, then broccoli in cheese sauce.
Mix together the water chestnuts, soup, mushrooms and mayonnaise; pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cover with onions and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: corny corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and sour cream; blend well.
Slowly add Jiffy corn bread mix.
Add the creamed corn, whole corn and crumbled bacon.
Spread in a square baking pan (grease pan).
Sprinkle cheese over top and spread evenly.
Bake, uncovered, 50 minutes to 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Soak the cracklings in real hot water.
Mix the meal, oil and salt; add crushed cracklings.
Make into pones and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: oven chicken and vegetable
directions: In a 2-quart shallow casserole, combine celery, carrot and onion.
Season chicken.
Place over vegetables.
Combine catsup and mustard (spread over chicken).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.
May serve with a baked potato and baked apple for a complete meal!
